title: candy kiss pecan cake
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature. Cream together margarine and sugar. Add eggs and mix well. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and vanilla. Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured tube pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 of pecans. Add remaining batter; push chocolate kisses into batter with teaspoon. Sprinkle with remaining pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. (Candy will sink to bottom of cake.) Cool 5 minutes in pan.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: yummy carrots
directions: Pare carrots and cut in julienne strips.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Cook carrots, covered in bouillon for 10 minutes.
Melt butter; add onions, sliced and cook covered for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add carrots with liquid.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add sugar.
Serves 6.

title: cornbake casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain.
Combine all ingredients; mix well and pour into one large or two small casserole dishes.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with margarine.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherries in snow
directions: Cook water and rice, covered, for 15 minutes over medium heat. Add 3 cups milk, oleo and sugar.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until thick.
Soften gelatin in 1/3 cup milk and add to rice.
Cook 3 minutes longer.
Remove and add almond extract. Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill and spread cherry pie filling over the top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat
eggs
and
sugar	together.
Add	syrup, vanilla, pecans, salt and butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake
for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinated steak
directions: Place round steak in nonmetal container large enough so it will lay flat.
Sprinkle with meat tenderizer; poke in with a fork.
Sprinkle with garlic powder; poke in with a fork.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and soy sauce; poke in with a fork.
Turn steak over; repeat sprinkling and poking.
Cover container; refrigerate for 1 to 3 days.
Cook over medium coals on the grill.
It can also be broiled in the oven, but the grill is the best.

title: pineapple sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a casserole dish.
Cut potatoes into thirds lengthwise and place in dish.
Combine sugars and cornstarch; stir in lemon juice, butter and pineapple.
Bring mixture to a boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Then pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated.

title: homemade cookies 'n cream ice cream
directions: In large bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Fold in cookies and whipped cream.
Pour into 2-quart container.
Cover.
Freeze until firm (approximately 6 hours). Makes 1 1/2 quarts ice cream; can easily be doubled.

title: coconut pie
directions: In 2-quart double boiler, combine sugar and cornstarch. Add beaten
yolks
and milk.
Add vanilla; stir and cook until thick. Remove
from
stove
and
add
oleo and coconut.
Stir until melted.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: potato casserole
directions: Quarter potatoes and cook with onions until tender.
Drain potatoes and mix with sour cream and butter.
Spread half of potato mixture in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over mixture, then layer with potato mixture, mushrooms and bacon crumbs and top with Velveeta cheese slices.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls and press down with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: poor man's brunch
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook peas and carrots.
Drain.
Add cream of chicken soup, whole milk and chicken bouillon.
Heat over medium heat until hot.
Serve on toasted English muffins.
Garnish with sliced tomatoes and shredded cheese for that "fancy look" or try over pasta instead for a more hearty fair.

title: barbecued pecans
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan; add Worcestershire sauce, catsup and hot sauce.
Stir in nuts; spoon into a glass baking dish, spreading evenly.
Bake at 400° (preheat) about 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Turn out on absorbent towels and sprinkle with salt.
Yields 25 servings.

title: sawmill gravy
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Reserve 2 tablespoons drippings and return to pan.
Blend in flour to make roux.
Add milk and blend until smooth.
Add sausage and bring back to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Serve over baking powder biscuits.

title: penna dutch shoo-fly cakes
directions: Put the soda into the molasses and boiling water slowly.
Pour liquid into a 9-inch pie crust.

title: chow chow
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and salt to fast boil.
Add all chopped vegetables and return to boil.
Cook 7 minutes.
Pack into jars. Process in hot water bath for 30 minutes.

title: sloppy jacques
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain off fat.
Sprinkle flour over meat and stir until the flour disappears.
Stir in undiluted soup.
Simmer 2 minutes or until thickened and hot.
Serve on buns.

title: garden spiral salad
directions: Cook pasta spirals in 4 quarts of boiling water (salt if desired) for 9 to 11 minutes or until tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water to cool.
Combine the remaining ingredients, except for the Italian dressing, and chill.
When ready to serve, toss the salad mixture with the Italian dressing.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and salt.
Heat until butter melts; cool to 105°.
Add yeast and stir until dissolves.
Place flour in bowl.
Make well and pour in liquid; blend well.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Roll on floured surface to 1/4-inch thick; cut into 3-inch squares.
Melt 1 stick butter; dip each square in butter and arrange in a 10-inch pan.
At this point, you may refrigerate overnight and let rise 2 hours or let rise 30 minutes. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Takes about 3 hours from start to finish.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions; drain grease.
Add chili powder and cook for 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar, eggs, nuts and dates.
Cook 10 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and Rice Krispies and stir.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over beans, pepper and onions.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix again before serving.

title: oreo freak-out
directions: Place crushed cookies in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Layer ice cream over crumbs.
Pour ice cream toppings on top of ice cream. Top with whipped topping.
Freeze.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small frying pan, fry bacon until clear.
Add the margarine and remaining ingredients except the shrimp.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Place the unpeeled shrimp in an open baking dish and pour sauce over the top.
Stir once to coat all of the shrimp.
Bake in an uncovered dish for 20 minutes, stirring twice during the baking process.
Serve hot.
Peel shrimp and enjoy.
Great over rice or as is.
Serves 6.

title: rice vegetable casserole
directions: Vegetables can be fresh, canned, frozen (any or all).

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, vanilla and eggs.
Add bananas.
Sift together all dry ingredients and alternate with buttermilk into banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: doughnuts
directions: Sift flour, then measure.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Stir lightly and add melted lard.
Roll on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Drop into hot lard and turn as doughnuts come to the top. Continue frying until doughnuts are golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Yields 4 dozen doughnuts.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta.
At the end of boiling, add peas.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss.
Cool and serve.
Good at suppers and reunions.
Makes large salad.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Separate onion rings and cover with cold water and ice cubes for 1 hour.
Mix together the flour, salt, sugar and baking powder. Add milk and beaten eggs to make a batter.
Coat onion slices with batter. Fry in deep fat over medium heat until golden brown.
Drain and serve at once.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: different kind of cheese cake
directions: Grease, don't flour, 9 x 12-inch dish.
Mix cup mix (minus 1 cup), oil and 1 egg.
Will be crumbly.
Pat into the greased dish up about 3/4 way on sides.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add 3 eggs and the 1 cup of reserved cake mix.
Mix on medium speed 1 minute.
Add milk, vanilla and lemon juice gradually beating 1 minute on low speed until smooth.
Pour into prepared crust. Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes or until not shaky in the middle.
Cool.
Top with 1 can cherry pie filling.
Chill overnight in the refrigerator.
Store in refrigerator.

title: you name it cake
directions: Line a 9 x 12-inch baking pan with foil.
Grease foil well. Pour in pineapple, juice and all.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle coconut over cake mix.
Put chopped nuts over coconut.
Do not stir any of this.
Leave in layers.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pizzaiola steak with pasta
directions: In medium saucepan, combine steak, oil, parsley, salt, pepper, tomatoes, water and garlic.
Cook over medium-low heat for approximately 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook pasta according to directions on package; drain.
Pour sauce over pasta. Garnish with steak and Parmesan cheese.

title: our best sunday chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken on heavy-duty foil or chicken may be placed in large baking dish instead of wrapping in foil.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In buttered casserole dish, crumble Ritz crackers in bottom of dish, then put in mixed vegetables, rice, meat, broccoli and cheese soup.
Put in rest of butter; crumble Ritz crackers on top. Add a little water so as not to stick.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: orange sherbet ice cream
directions: Mix together and churn in a one gallon container. Great!

title: mexicali chicken(feeds 2 people)
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet (I use an iron one).
Put in chicken and onions, stirring frequently until done.
While this is cooking, start the spaghetti cooking in boiling water.
Add garlic powder and other spices to chicken/onion mixture.
Stir well to coat chicken.
Add tomatoes (I like to chop mine before adding). Simmer while spaghetti is cooking.
Drain spaghetti, pour the chicken mixture over it and enjoy!

title: sweet kraut
directions: Rinse kraut really good with cold water; drain well.
Can also add kielbasa or Italian sausage and simmer in crock-pot.

title: little stickies
directions: Bring water, brown sugar and butter to boil or melt in microwave.
Put syrup in bottom of cake pan (13 x 9-inch). Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon on rectangles formed by 2 triangles of crescent rolls.
Roll up and cut into 6 slices. Place on top of syrup.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn upside-down on foil.

title: coconut pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Keep the egg whites for topping.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to egg whites; beat.
Beat yellow of eggs and mix with all other ingredients.
Cook over burning eye until thickened.
Pour into a pie crust.
Now pour egg white mixture over pie.
Bake at 350° until top is browned.

title: light and moist plum pudding
directions: Mix suet, eggs and corn syrup.
Sift dry ingredients and add in turn with water; stir in remaining ingredients.
Fill well-greased 1 1/2-quart mold 2/3 full.
Cover tightly; steam 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with hot Lemon-Nutmeg Sauce (recipe follows).

title: johnny cake
directions: Mix all ingredients to consistency of mashed potatoes, adding more liquid if necessary.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot greased griddle to make cakes 1/2-inch thick by 2 1/2-inches across.
Fry 6 to 8 minutes on each side until there is a brown crunch crust and the inside is done.
Makes 12.
Serve with butter or maple syrup or both.

title: tiropita
directions: Hand blend all ingredients until well mixed.
Butter a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add 10 layers, buttering each sheet.
Pour 1/2 of the filling; cover with a sheet of filo.
Pour remaining filling, then cover with filo, buttering each sheet.
Bake at 350° for about an hour until golden brown.

title: dent-the-diet pie
directions: Mix sugars and flour.
Blend in butter.
In another bowl, mix eggs, vanilla and syrup; add to sugar mixture.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake until almost firm at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken breast chunks with mushrooms and lemon
directions: Cut chicken into bite size chunks and season with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet; add chicken and brown all over.
Add garlic and saute 5 minutes over medium heat.
Turn chicken pieces over.
Add lemon slices, mushrooms, wine, oregano and parsley. Season lightly with salt and pepper.
Cook chicken over low heat, partially covered, for 10 minutes.
Serve with favorite vegetable.

title: crisp mustard-baked pork chops
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Make the bread into crumbs in a blender or food processor.
Melt the butter.
Combine the bread crumbs, 1/2 tsp. salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper.
Stir in the butter. Coat both sides of the pork chops with mustard.
Put in a shallow roasting pan.
Distribute crumb mixture over chops and pat lighly so it clings.
Bake until browned, about 30 minutes.

title: nan's banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, beating thoroughly. Add mashed bananas to this mixture gradually with buttermilk and vanilla.
Add nuts and chopped cherries.
Bake at about 300° until done.
Use either 2 loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/4 x 2 1/2-inch) or a square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Loaf pans make 8 to 10 slices each. With the square pan, cut into squares and serve with whipped cream and a cherry.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a medium bowl and mix well. Whisk eggs in a large bowl until blended. Add sugar, oil, vanilla and lemon zest and mix well. Stir the dry ingredients into egg mixture until blended. Chill, covered, for 30 minutes or longer.

title: wild rice
directions: Mix together and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to jello.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: spanish pintos
directions: Soak and cook beans until tender, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer slowly a few minutes and serve hot.

title: hot wassail
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Strain through a cheesecloth and serve hot.
Serves 12.

title: colonial bread
directions: Place cornmeal in
bowl.
Carefully
pour boiling water into bowl
on cornmeal.	Stir
until
smooth.
Let
stand
30 minutes. Stir in salt,
butter
and molasses.
Mix with flour and
yeast. Let
rise until double in bulk.
Punch down. Form into
loaf
and place in large loaf pan.
Let rise again. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 1 (1 1/2 pound) loaf.

title: german sour cream twists
directions: Sift flour and salt into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir into flour mixture with sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well with hand.
Cover with damp cloth and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: almost crab cakes
directions: Mix and make into cakes. Fry in bacon grease.

title: cheesy pinto bean dip
directions: Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray and heat until hot. Saute tomatoes 2 minutes.
Meanwhile, mince garlic in food processor if available.
Otherwise, chop finely and then add to blender.
Add onion, salsa and beans.
Scrape sides of blender or processor and pulse until smooth.
Pour processed beans in skillet with tomatoes and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts and serve warm. Serve with celery sticks or baked tortilla chips.

title: harriett brown's mom's dressing
directions: Mix all the ingredients together; place in pan or in the bird. Cook 2 hours at 350° in oven.

title: mal's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix both sugars, oil, eggs and vanilla and add the dry ingredients slowly while stirring. Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet to make large cookies. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: very good cereal cookies
directions: Butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat corn syrup, butter and chocolate chips to boiling in a 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in a large mixing bowl.
Toss quickly until completely coated. Fold in marshmallows, one cup at a time.
Press mixture evenly into a pan with a buttered-back spoon.
Let stand until firm, at least one hour.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 48 squares.

title: just my brownies
directions: Mix for three minutes in bowl.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: never fail divinity icing
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water together until it spins a thread. Beat the egg whites stiff.
Pour cooked mixture over eggs slowly, beating constantly.
When stiff, add powdered sugar and vanilla. The powdered sugar is the secret to success in this icing.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt; let stand 3 hours.
Drain. Combine seasoning and vinegar and boil.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Heat to simmering and pack hot.
Be careful to avoid boiling as that makes pickles soft.
Pack while hot in clean jars and seal immediately.

title: charlotte's dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Stir into cheese mixture the dried beef, onion, green pepper or celery and the pepper, mixing well.
Stir in sour cream.
Pour into an 8-inch pie plate and sprinkle walnuts over top.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Serve hot with oblong (Waverly) crackers; use to dip into the hot mixture.

title: basic bread
directions: Moisten yeast in water water; add honey, oil, salt and flour. (For variation, also add 1 to 2 cups oatmeal, wheat cereal, etc.) Let sit 1/2 hour or until sponge forms.
Mix in 5 to 6 cups flour and knead until smooth.
Cover with warm damp cloth and let rise until double.
Mix down and let rise again.
Form into 3 loaves; let rise again.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until golden.
Bake at 375° in oven.

title: taco pasta shells
directions: Cook ground beef in a skillet until brown; drain.
Add taco seasoning; prepare according to package directions.
Add cream cheese; cover and simmer for 5 minutes until cream cheese is melted into meat mixture.
Stir to blend.
Allow mixture to cool.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoonful and flatten. Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Recipe does not call for flour.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Double soups and onion mix for larger roasts.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Cream margarine in mixing bowl.
Add cocoa and powdered sugar alternately with milk.
Beat to spreading consistency.
Blend in vanilla.
Makes 2 cups.

title: orange muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then sifted dry ingredients alternately with juice.
Add vanilla.
Bake in
greased muffin tins at 350°.

title: lovely lemon cheesecake
directions: Spray 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan or 9-inch pie plate lightly with nonstick cooking spray; sprinkle bottom and sides with the graham cracker crumbs.

title: beets a l'orange
directions: Combine rind, juice, salt and cornstarch in double boiler. Cook and stir until thickened.
Add beets and heat thoroughly. Sprinkle with pepper and serve.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Place marshmallow cream and chocolate kissed in a bowl. Set aside. Combine sugar, milk and margarine in a pan and bring to a boil. Boil for 8 minutes. Pour over marshmallow cream and kisses. Stir until blended then blend in pecans. Drop by tsp. on wax paper. Makes 12 dozen.

title: roxanna's carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and lightly hand beat. Add flour and other ingredients.
Beat lightly again.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the powdered sugar in an electric blender.
Blend thoroughly.
Shape mixture into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: layered ambrosia
directions: Arrange half the orange sections in a glass bowl; top with grapefruit, 1/4 cup coconut, pineapple and remaining orange sections.
Drizzle with honey and sprinkle with 1/4 cup coconut. Cover and chill 8 hours.

title: berry pie
directions: Mix all berries, white sugar and cinnamon.
Put in pie crust. Cook the 5 cups tapioca and pour over the berry mix.
Mix the 2 cups flour, 1 1/2 cups brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter.
Spoon over pie.
Cook 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: okara(bean curd residue dish)
directions: Cut
mushrooms	in
small
strips and boil (in water in which mushrooms have been soaked) together with shrimp for 10 minutes. Add
carrots
and
beans
until tender.
Season with shoyu,
salt, sugar
and
gourmet powder and cook few minutes longer.
Heat
a large skillet, adding oil.	Add the vegetable mixture
and	stir in	the okara until well blended, stirring constantly to prevent burning on the bottom.
Add green onions a few minutes before removing from stove.
Okara should be dry and flaky.
It is also good and healthy!

title: rosy pear compote
directions: In saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon and ginger.
Bring to a boil.
Place pears and oranges in a baking dish and pour cooked mixture over fruit.
Cover and bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until tender.
Serve slightly warm as a side dish or place in pretty compotes and serve as a dessert with a dollop of whipped cream or ice cream on top.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in large pot.
Sprinkle with salt.
Top with ice cubes.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: almond cookies
directions: Blend butter, sugar and extract.
Mix in flour and nuts. Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° or 350° for about 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while they are still warm.

title: lobster with sauce(serves 1)
directions: Saute garlic and pepper in lemon juice until golden brown.
Add water, parsley and lobster; simmer for approximately 10 minutes.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Spread half the bread in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle half of the cream cheese over bread in pan.
Repeat, layering with remaining bread and cream cheese.
Whisk eggs, milk and syrup in large bowl.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Crumble candy bars with a rolling pin or in a food processor. Set a few crumbled pieces aside for garnish.
In a large glass or trifle bowl, break half of the brownies in pieces and place in bottom of bowl.
Cover the brownies with half of the prepared pudding, half of the crumbled candy pieces and half of the whipped topping; repeat.
Decorate with a few candy pieces and stemmed red cherries.
Serves 20 to 24 ladies or 10 to 12 men.

title: monster mix
directions: Mix ingredients and serve in cups.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine soup (undiluted), sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over carrots, onion and bell peppers.

title: chimayo corn pudding
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients real well. Butter 9 x 12 pan (casserole).
Pour half of batter. Add cheese and chilies. Cover with rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: stir fried pork
directions: In medium bowl, toss pork loin with 1/4 tsp. salt and pepper. In a large fry pan or wok, heat 1 Tbsp. oil.
Add half the pork and cook, stirring until browned, 2-3 minutes.
Remove, Repeat with another Tbsp. oil and remaining pork.
Remove.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients (except cheese).
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with cheese.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.

title: delicious pie
directions: Mix all the above ingredients and put into a 9-inch deep dish unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix flour, sugar and eggs; mix other ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°, turn down to 250° until pie shakes a little.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding muffin mix last.
Pour into well-greased iron skillet.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool on rack.
Remove from pan and keep in "icebox."
Wrap in foil and put in airtight container.
Keeps for 2 weeks.

title: chocolate sour cream cake a la terri
directions: Mix water, oil, cream and eggs together.
Add pudding and mix well.
Add cake mix and then fold in chocolate bits.
Grease baking pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Saute the onion in the oleo.
Mix remaining ingredients and add the onion and oleo.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses. Sift dry ingredients and mix into shortening mixture. Chill dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip into sugar and cinnamon.
Place 3-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake just until set, but not hard, about 10 to 12 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: ham loaf sandwiches
directions: Combine eggs, crackers, milk, sugar, vinegar, mustard and dash of pepper.
Mix in ham and pork.
Pat into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.
Drain off fat. Refrigerate in pan until well chilled.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Brown the ground beef and drain on paper towel.
Grease a large iron skillet. Sprinkle with a little corn meal and let it brown slightly.
Pour half of the corn meal mixture in skillet.
Add one at a time the cheese, meat, onion.
Pour in other half of corn meal mixture and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Makes about 48 cups of hot chocolate.	Store in airtight container.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon and cut into small pieces.
Add flour, mix with bacon and brown.
Set aside until potatoes are cooked.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and jam (beating until smooth).
Add soda to buttermilk and beat into mixture alternately with flour, mixed with spices.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° in 3 well-greased 8-inch pans for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: oreo cookie ice cream
directions: Mix well, then finish filling freezer with fresh milk and freeze.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in salad dish.
Refrigerate until firm set.

title: cream chicken in wine sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken, in baking dish.
Place chicken on top of soup mixture.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: clam chowder(serves 4)
directions: Pare and cube potatoes. Cover with water in medium saucepan. Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer until tender, but not too soft (about 15 minutes).
In large saucepan saute bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels, then crumble.
In drippings saute onion until golden.
Remove saucepan from heat and stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Add liquid to flour mixture gradually.
Stir until quite smooth.
Add drained, cooked potatoes, milk, cream, clams and bacon; heat through. Garnish with parsley flakes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and serve with vegetables.

title: one-step lasagna(cooking time:  34 to 37 minutes)
directions: Crumble beef or turkey in 2-quart microproof casserole.
Cover with casserole lid and cook on High for 5 minutes, stirring once during cooking time.
Pour off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce and mix well.

title: cheesy mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until done; drain and mash.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, butter, seasoning and onion; mix well.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cover last 15 minutes and put grated cheese on top.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine cocoa, flour and sugar; mix thoroughly.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk and eggs.
Cook either on top of stove, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from burner and add vanilla and margarine or cook in microwave oven on Medium for 5 minutes; stir.
Repeat and stir.
Cook 3 minutes on Medium-high and continue until thickened.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Top with Cool Whip or meringue.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs in bowl; gradually stir white and brown sugars into the eggs.
Stir corn meal and flour into egg mixture and then add milk and melted butter.
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream together cream cheese, 1/2 cup butter or margarine and vanilla.
Alternately beat in sugar and 1/3 cup milk.
Blend in chocolate.
Remove 2 cups for frosting.
Cover and refrigerate. Cream together remaining chocolate mixture and butter.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together dry ingrediiets; beat into creamed mixture alternately with the remaining milk.
Turn into two greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove; cool on rack. Remove frosting from refrigerator 15 minutes before frosting cake. Serves 8 to 10.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and salt in a heavy boiler and bring to a boil.
Boil a few seconds then add dates and cook over moderate high heat until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Stir in walnuts.
Stir by hand until cool enough to handle.
Shape, on was paper,
into 2 ten inch long rolls 1 1/2 inch in diameter.
Cool until firm and slice 1/4 inch thick.
Keep refrigerated.
Yield 7 dozen.

title: easy corn
directions: Melt a stick of butter in pan that corn is to be baked in. Mix ingredients except cheese.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, evaporated milk and eggs together real well.
Add bananas and vanilla to this mixture.
Fill with whole milk to full line, in a 1 1/2 gallon freezer.
Freeze until firm.

title: carrot potato casserole
directions: In a nonstick 8-inch square baking dish, layer the potatoes, then onion, then carrots. Salt and pepper layers.
Combine the soup with 1 can of water.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Serves 6.

title: aromatic cider
directions: Mix juices and place in 30-cup size percolator coffee pot. Place coffee filter in pot; spread spices and sugar in filter. Percolate until done.

title: cheese spread
directions: Stir together all ingredients until well mixed.
Chill.

title: hamburger and beer vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions until meat is browned; drain off fat.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook for 8 to 10 hours on low.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: mozzarella spaghetti skillet
directions: Combine beef, mushrooms, onions and green pepper in a large fry pan (preferably nonstick).
Saute over medium heat until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain fat.
Cut up tomatoes and add tomatoes and juice to pan.
Stir in water, seasoning and salt. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until pasta is cooked, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese, stir until melted. Serves 5 to 6.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Grind egg, pickle, pepper and onion. Add mayonnaise and catsup.
Mix thoroughly.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Toss all together and refrigerate.
Add dressing just before serving.

title: cold nacho
directions: Mix refried beans with taco seasoning.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream; spread over beans.
Spread remaining ingredients in layers over sour cream mixture.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: herman talmadge sweet potatoes
directions: Mix yams, sugar, vanilla, milk and butter in small casserole dish.
Set aside.

title: hot sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook about 1 hour.
Seal in jars.

title: sherry crabmeat quiche(perfect for a brunch!)
directions: Grease baking sheet.
Let dough warm to room temperature in its bag.
Once warm, place in baking sheet with towel covering it until dough rises, about 4 to 5 hours.

title: no fail pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add milk and flour.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla flavoring last.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: ensaladilla rusa with spanish mayonnaise
directions: Whisk egg yolk, lemon juice, mustard and salt and pepper to taste until the mixture has a creamy consistency.
Add oil, drop by drop, whisking continually by hand or in a blender.
Final consistency should be very thick. For the typically Spanish touch, beat an egg white and fold into mayonnaise to make base for Ensaladilla Rusa.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Combine oil and flour over medium heat.
Cook until thickened. Add salt and chili powder.
Dip tortillas in sauce.
Fill with grated cheese, onion and olives.
Bake in
moderate oven until bubbly.

title: creamy jello mold
directions: Add lime Jell-O to 1 1/2 cups water; stir to dissolve.
Add pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Refrigerate until set. Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water, stirring to dissolve.
Set aside.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Prepare Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Then add frozen strawberries.
If berries do not have any water, add 1 cup cold water.
Add 4 packages sugar or sugar-free sweetener.
When this is mixed it will start to congeal.
Then pinch off bits of angel food cake and add to berries mixture.
Put in a square 8 x 8-inch dish and store overnight in refrigerator.
When removed, top with Cool Whip.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda together in a large bowl.
Cut in butter until mixtures is crumbly.
Add egg, orange peel and orange juice all at once.
Stir until mixture is evenly moist.
Fold in cranberries and nuts. Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups, 2/3 full.

title: sloppy joe's
directions: Chop up hamburger while cooking it in a medium size saucepan. Drain off grease.
Add catsup, mustard and soup.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix together, add chicken and marinate overnight.
Turn over once.
Broil 7-8 minutes on each side, depending on thickness.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar and syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture begins to bubble. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well blended.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: zucchini rice casserole
directions: Fry bacon; crumble.
Discard drippings (set aside).
Saute onion with butter; add chopped zucchini.
Blend in cream of mushroom soup, milk, rice and cheese.
Mix well.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a large oblong 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with crumbled bacon and serve.

title: little wieners
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot or slow cooker to heat through and keep warm.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into freezer.
Finish filling to line with milk. Enjoy!

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into uncooked pie crust (9 or 10-inch).
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes then reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes or until silver knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: spiced mixed fruit
directions: Combine sugar, water, rosemary, cinnamon and cloves in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Remove from heat; cool and strain.
In mixing bowl, combine pineapple, apples, orange sections and lemon juice.
Pour strained syrup over fruit and mix well.
Chill.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate truffle cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs and 2 Tbsp. butter. Press onto bottom of greased 9 inch spring form pan. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes. Mix cream cheese, sugar, and vanilla on medium speed until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing on low speed after each addition, just until blended. Blend in melted chocolate and liqueur. Pour over crust. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until center is almost set. Run knife or metal spatula around rim or pan to loosen cake. Cool before removing rim of pan. Refrigerate.

title: french cream chocolate frosting
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Gradually add confectioners sugar, creaming well.
Add egg; mix thoroughly.
Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Beat until of spreading consistency.
Thin with milk, if necessary.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and flavor.
Add self-rising flour and 1/2 cup sweet milk.
Then add plain flour and the rest of the milk.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Use tube pan, greased and floured.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Add rest of ingredients.
Rinse out chili bottle with water and add.
Simmer until thickened.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion, bell pepper and celery in bacon grease until brown. Season with salt and pepper. Add ground beef and cook until brown. Add remaining ingredients, cooking over low heat for about 2 hours. Pour over cooked spaghetti and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: rice pudding
directions: Barely cover rice with cold water and simmer very slowly until rice absorbs all the water; the rice should only be partially cooked.
Bring the quart of milk to a scald and blend partially cooked rice and milk together.
Continue cooking very slowly until rice is thoroughly cooked.

title: sardine and cheese sandwich
directions: Note:
Sardines can should be a double layer can.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Stir together peanut butter and margarine.
Gradually add sugar, stirring until combined.
Shape into 1 inch balls; place on waxed paper.
Set aside.
Melt confectioners coating. Place small amounts of chocolate in bottom of candy cups.
Let cool, then put peanut butter balls in candy cups and smash with thumb.
Then put more chocolate over the top of peanut butter balls.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour salad and milk into 2 quart casserole.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and thyme.
Place biscuits over chicken mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with mixer until well blended. Shape into ball and roll in crushed salted peanuts.
Serve with apple slices or crackers.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix well and pour into well-greased and floured 1 pound coffee can.
Will fill 3 coffee cans or 2 (5 x 9-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes good muffins (36 to 40).
Bake about 20 minutes in 350° regular oven or in the microwave bake 6 for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, turning once.

title: 7-up cake
directions: To bake Herman, combine first 11 ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch or 2 jelly roll pans or muffin pans.
Before baking, sprinkle with 1 tablespoon flour, 1 tablespoon cinnamon, brown sugar and 1/4 cup butter crumbled together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
If desired, drizzle with icing mixture of powdered sugar, milk and vanilla while cake is warm.

title: corned beef salad loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl (except pumpernickel and party rye).
Cut out loaf and scoop mixture into loaf.
Reserve inside of loaf (cut up) for dipping.
Serve with party rye.
Best if made and chilled for several hours before serving or overnight.

title: baked butternut squash
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour; beat in.
Add squash, vanilla and lemon; mix well.
Melt margarine in baking dish; add to mixture and stir in.
Pour all into dish.
Sprinkle with mace before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove when firm from a gentle shake.
Serves 6.

title: noodles
directions: Knead; roll out and cut as noodles.
Cook in chicken or beef broth.

title: gladys rowe pafford's cream cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar and eggs (one at a time).
Add vanilla, milk and instant pudding; mix well.
Add baking powder to flour, then mix into the first mixture a small portion at a time.
Make layers.
Bake at 350° to 375° until done.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Combine and mix cake mix, jello, eggs and oil until smooth. Fold in blackberries.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Or bake in sheet pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Cool and frost.

title: festive punch
directions: Pour lemonade into punch bowl and stir in raspberries and strawberries.
Add ginger ale and ice.
Stir in sherbet.
Serves 10.

title: cherry streusel pie
directions: Spoon cherries over bottom of pie shell.
Mix all remaining ingredients, except Streusel Topping.
Pour over cherries.
Bake for 10 minutes in 450° oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.
Prepare Streusel Topping.
Remove pie from oven.
Sprinkle topping over pie and bake until topping is lightly browned, 10 to 15 minutes. Cool.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion and eggs.
Combine and mix remaining ingredients.
Mix all together gently.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix thoroughly; pour over vegetables and stir. Refrigerate overnight.

title: brownies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add the eggs and beat.
Sift the flour and cocoa.
Add the vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tabbouleh(crushed wheat, tomato, mint and parsley salad)
directions: Place the bulgur in a bowl or pan.
Pour in enough cold water to cover it completely.
Let it soak for 10 minutes.
Drain in a sieve lined with a double thickness of dampened cheesecloth.
Wrap the bulgur in the cheesecloth and squeeze until dry.
Place bulgur into a deep bowl.
Add the tomatoes, parsley, onions, lemon juice and salt.
Toss gently but thoroughly together with fork.
Just before serving, stir in olive oil and mint.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato waffles
directions: Blend the potatoes, egg yolks and milk until smooth.
Add the cake flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Whip 3 egg whites until peak.
Stir 1/4 of whites in first, then stir in the rest of the whites.
Add the melted butter.
Pour into iron.

title: banana crunch cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in eggs and bananas.
Add combined dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, mixing well after each addition. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hamburger-tomato-veggie soup
directions: Cook the hamburger with part of the onion soup package. Season to taste with Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper, celery seed and garlic. Combine all ingredients and let simmer about 2 hours.

title: torte d'maize
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Let cool about 10 minutes before serving.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine apples, pecans and sugar; let stand for 1 hour, stirring often.
Do not drain.
Combine flour and spices.
Add apple mixture and stir well.
Stir in margarine, vanilla and eggs. Spoon batter into two greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Bake in two loaf pans.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Place hominy in casserole dish; add chopped onion.
Sprinkle corn chips over this and then add cream of mushroom soup.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheese chowder
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to serving temperature. Makes 18 servings.

title: sweet potato pone or souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serve hot or cold with a spoonful of vanilla ice cream.

title: homestyle breakfast delight
directions: Melt margarine in a large frying pan; add potatoes and onion. Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally to brown evenly, for about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden.
Add Nuteena and sprinkle mixture with parsley.
Reduce heat.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Combine all in mixing bowl.
Add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Stir dough down and place in a well-greased 1 1/2-quart round or oval casserole dish.
Let rise in warm place until dough is at the top of bowl.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until a very golden brown.
Brush with soft butter upon removing from oven.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Stir in eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Alternate potatoes, meat, onions, peppers, cheese and mushroom soup in a greased casserole dish. Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of 2 quart bowl.
Cover with crumbs. Mix pudding and milk for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 mixture on crumbs, put a thin layer of more crumbs on pudding mix, put remaining pudding in bowl and top with a layer of crumbs.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: strawberry cheese pies
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add Eagle Brand milk and mix well.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour in a graham cracker crust.
Let chill 3 hours, then top with pie filling (make 2 pies).

title: texas hamburgers
directions: Mix together and shape into patties.
Are best when chilled and can be frozen.
These grill great.

title: dream whip dessert
directions: Whip egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy.
Slowly add sugar and beat until very stiff.
Fold in crackers, nuts and vanilla into egg white mixture.
Hand mix.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top will have a crust.
Let set until cold.

title: payday bars
directions: Heat Karo syrup and sugar in microwave 30 seconds; stir. Heat 3 1/2 minutes more then add peanut butter. Stir in peanuts and Crispix.
Spread onto large greased cookie sheet. Cool and cut into bars.

title: grammi's pancakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add liquid ingredients and 1 teaspoon vanilla when you are ready to bake.
Bake on slightly greased surface.

title: pierogi in a shell
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
In another pan, cook shells.
While cooking, saute onions in butter; then set aside.
Drain potatoes, mash and add salt, pepper and some milk.
Add grated cheese and 2 to 3 tablespoons onion mixture to mashed potatoes.
Beat well.

title: honey nut rolls
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix milk, oil, syrup and salt in a bowl; cool to lukewarm and add lemon rind and yeast mixture. Beat in the flour gradually.
Let rise until double in bulk, then punch down the dough and pat out on a floured board into a long sheet, about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with honey and cover with nuts.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Cut in 1-inch slices; arrange on a baking sheet or in greased muffin tins.
Let rise until almost double (30 minutes), then bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Delicious!

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir until just combined.

title: certain jingle biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dump flour, sugar and baking powder in bowl. Sift 2 or 3 times.
Cut in shortening.
Blend until of coarse cornmeal texture.
Add buttermilk; stir about 12 strokes until well mixed and loose from sides of bowl.
Turn onto floured surface.
Sprinkle flour over dough.
Knead for about 30 seconds, not too much.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut.
Place on heavily greased pan.
Place in oven.
Bake until light brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt margarine and baste biscuits when done.

title: apple sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and slice into bite-size pieces.
Add sausage to apple slices and mix.
Mix brown sugar and spices with enough liquid to make saucy.
Put into a baking dish in a circle around desired filling and bake at 350° for 1 hour until apples are done.

title: apricot stars
directions: Mix ingredients well and make 3 balls of dough.
Wrap in wax paper overnight.
Next day roll out dough with a little flour and sugar.
Cut out about 3-inch squares and slit each corner.
Place 1/2 teaspoon apricots in center and fold over to center.
Bake at about 325° until done.
Continue with other dough.

title: apple and pineapple salad
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar and eggs in pineapple juice; use whip. Add marshmallow cream; add crushed pineapple and set aside to cool. Using a mixer, whip the cream.
After thickened, use full speed. After mixture is cool, blend with the whipped cream.
Add apples.

title: summer corn relish
directions: In large Dutch oven combine sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed and turmeric.
Heat to boiling; add remaining ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Pack in hot scalded jars; seal.
Makes 3 pints.

title: shrimp salad with peas(serves 6)
directions: Clean cooked shrimp, peel and devein.
Thin mayonnaise with cream and mix all ingredients together.
Season with Old Bay and dry mustard.
Serve on top of lettuce.

title: lemon buttered broccoli
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and stir in arrowroot.
Add lemon juice and water; cook the mixture over moderate heat until it simmers. Stir in the food coloring a drop at a time until sauce is buttery yellow; serve sauce over hot broccoli.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix together mashed potatoes, salt and vanilla.
Add enough sugar to make it firm enough to hold it's shape.
On wax paper sprinkled with sugar, roll out mixture into a rectangle, 16 x 9 inches and 1/8 inch thick.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up dough lengthwise in wax paper.
Chill 30 minutes or longer.
When ready, slice in 1/2-inch pieces.

title: french dressing(makes 1 quart.)
directions: Mix all together. Ready for use.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the fruits and marshmallows in a large bowl.
Mix in the Cool Whip.

title: mrs. nulty's famous egg rolls
directions: Cook turkey meat.
Season with garlic salt.
Add teriyaki, oyster sauce and water.
Let simmer for a few minutes.
Add vegetables.
Mix. Cook for a few minutes.
Drain and cool.
Wrap in egg roll wrappers.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together until creamy the sugars and shortening.
Add egg, water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add oats to mixture.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients to mixture and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonsful or roll in ball about the size of a walnut.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press down lightly.
Bake in oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly brown.
Yields about 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water.
Stir in 2 2/3 cups warm water, the sugar, salt, shortening and 5 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour to make dough easy to handle. Turn dough onto lightly floured board; knead about 10 minutes. Place in greased bowl, greased side up.
Cover; let rise about 1 hour or until double in size.
Punch down dough and form into loaf.
Place in greased pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Bread will sound hollow when tapped. Butter and serve.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Mix egg, milk and oil together.
Combine dry and liquids together.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Gently stir blueberries into batter.
Fill greased or lined muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: kugelis(serves 20)
directions: Chop onions and bacon fine.
Start frying bacon; when bacon is partially cooked, add all the onions.
Continue cooking until the onions are transparent.
Add one stick of butter or margarine.
Set aside.
Peel potatoes and set in cold water until ready to grate. Grate potatoes on fine grater, occasionally adding evaporated milk. Use entire can.
Helps prevent browning.
Add bacon, onions and butter to grated potatoes.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat eggs and add to potatoes.
Mix; add enough milk to reach the consistency of pancake batter.
Grease two 9 x 12-inch pans.
Pour in mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add cubes and stir until dissolved.
Add steak (may be substituted with your favorite beef).
Cut vegetables into bite-sized chunks.
Add to beef stock.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Boil until vegetables are cooked through.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine egg, cream, sugar and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
When mixed, put in can, add condensed milk; stir.
Add regular milk to fill line on freezer can.

title: cousin tib's peas and water chestnuts(an interesting vegetable dish for a large group)
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat; add onions, celery and red pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, until tender. Stir in peas and next 4 ingredients. Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with noodles. Heat thoroughly, about 20 minutes, in 350° oven. Serves 18 to 22.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, reserving onion rings for topping.
Place in a greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Shred cheese.
Add 2 or 3 jars of diced pimentos with juice. Stir in several spoonfuls of mustard along with a couple of good shakes of Worcestershire sauce.
After mixing well, add enough mayonnaise to make it spreadable.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and molasses.
Beat well.
Mix soda with sour milk.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour milk.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: krispy pralines
directions: Mix eggs,
sugar, oil and vanilla. Gradually add flour. Mix well, then
add
Rice Krispies and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: calico relish
directions: Coarsely grind cucumbers, carrots and onions; stir in salt. Let stand 3 hours; drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Add drained vegetables and simmer for 30 minutes uncovered.
Put in pint jars and seal.
This is real good in potato salad or tuna salad as well as just eating as a relish or with hot dogs.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and eggs.
Add vanilla to sour cream.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda; add alternately to sugar mixture and sour cream mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll out on pastry cloth 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with large cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar and press lightly.
Bake in oven at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 100 (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: black bean soup
directions: Heat oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Saute onion, celery, carrots and garlic for 5 minutes. Season with chili powder, cumin, and black pepper; cook for 1 minute. Stir in vegetable broth, 2 cans of beans, and corn. Bring to a boil. Meanwhile, in a food processor or blender, process remaining 2 cans beans and tomatoes until smooth. Stir into boiling soup mixture, reduce heat to medium, and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Take deboned chicken and put in bowl; add soup, cut up eggs and broth mix. Put in casserole dish. In another bowl, mix flour and soft butter, then add milk. Mix well and pour over top of chicken mixture. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: curried fruit
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Pour over fruit.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: nutty banana shake
directions: Combine ingredients in blender; mix well (until smooth).
Pour into tall glasses.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: sweet potatoes souffle
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Add all other ingredients.
Mash and mix well.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven, cover top with marshmallows.
Bake until golden brown.

title: princess perfect dessert
directions: Pour boiling water into blender.
Add gelatin and blend at low speed until dissolved, about 30 seconds.
Combine milk and ice to make 1 1/4 cups; stir in blender until partially melted.
Add sliced banana; blend until smooth.
Spoon into dessert dishes. Chill until set, at least 30 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add chicken broth. Cook and stir until thick.
Stir in cream.
Add sherry and salt.

title: cheese meatballs
directions: Combine chopped chuck, corn flakes and 1/4 cup milk, salt and catsup.
Form into meatballs, then saute in 1 tablespoon of oil until brown on both sides.
Arrange in baking dish.

title: roquefort cheese stuffed baked potatoes(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Wash and dry potatoes; bake until soft, 45 to 60 minutes.
Cut a slice from the top of each potato and scoop out the potato, being careful not to break skin.
Mash well; beat in sour cream, Roquefort cheese, salt and pepper.
Add more sour cream to make fluffy.
Stir in green onions.
Spoon mixture into shells, mounding slightly.
Place on baking sheet.
Dust with paprika; return to oven to brown.

title: tortellini picnic salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions. Drain. Transfer to a large bowl. Add artichoke hearts, tomato, feta, olives and walnuts. Set aside.

title: four bean salad
directions: Wash and prepare navy beans. Drain and chill. Drain canned beans. Combine with navy beans in a large bowl.
Add green pepper and onion.
Mix oil and vinegar with sugar, salt and pepper. Pour over bean mixture and toss.
Refrigerate.

title: good cake
directions: Mix mandarins in cake mix. Do not drain because you do not add water to mix. The juice from oranges is plenty. Put eggs and Crisco as shown on box. "No water." Bake 3 thin layers.

title: date puffs
directions: Melt oleo in a 10-inch skillet.
Add sugar.
Quickly stir in egg yolks and continue stirring over low heat until mixture thickens.
Add chopped dates; mash and stir until thickened. Remove from heat and cool.
Add nuts and cereal.
Mix well.
Form into small balls and dust in a bag with sifted confectioners sugar.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: coconut chip cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place crushed graham crackers in bottom.
Place in even layers the remaining dry ingredients. Drizzle milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares while still warm.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Add 1 cup hot water in jello and cool.
Beat sugar and egg together.
Whip cream and add strawberries, then jello and nuts. Line large pan with vanilla wafers.
Add strawberry mixture.
Top with rolled cookies.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Cool for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pumpkin walnut cake
directions: On waxed paper, sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.

title: pork for a king
directions: Wash roast; season with pepper, salt and garlic.
Put in crock-pot on low; add orange and cranberries.
Cook for 6 hours. Serve over cooked rice, using juice from roast as gravy.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan, cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
In a skillet, cook ground beef, sausage, celery, onion and garlic until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat from skillet.
Stir in oregano, pepper and cream cheese.
Cook and stir over low heat to melt cheese.
Gradually add Cheddar and Gouda cheeses, stirring and heating until cheeses are nearly melted.
Add tomato sauce and stir.
Remove from heat.
Stir together cottage cheese and egg.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and serve with vegetables for a dip or serve as a dressing on mixed garden salad.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix and pudding mix.
Add eggs, oil, orange juice, liqueur Galliano and vodka.
Beat on low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute.
Beat on medium speed for 5 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into a greased and floured fluted 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; pour on glaze while still warm.

title: curried rice casserole
directions: Grease casserole with butter, combine rice, celery, onion, water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, salt, curry powder, chicken soup and 1 1/2 cups of the water.
Mix well and pour into casserole. Place chicken breasts on top, cover casserole, bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.
Add the remaining water after mixture has cooked for 1 hour.

title: boiled chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken, celery, onion, salt, pepper and bouillon until chicken is tender and you have a good chicken broth.
Remove fat, bones and skin from cooked chicken; set broth aside for later use. Mix flour and Crisco until well blended.
Add eggs until you have a sticky yellow dough (must be sticky).
Roll out on a well-floured board until very thin.
Cut into small bite-size squares.
Bring chicken broth to boil.
Add potatoes and then drop squares of dough one at a time into broth.
Cook for 20 minutes, stirring frequently, or until tender.
Add boned chicken and simmer until chicken is heated.
If necessary, add more salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with a vegetable.

title: bread pie
directions: Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of flour and 1/2 cup of sugar in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle light layer of biscuit crumbs in shell. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar and 1 tablespoon of flour over biscuit crumbs.
Pour milk over, just to cover, 2 to 3 tablespoons of butter, more or less.
Pour Milnot over all.
Sprinkle quite a bit of cinnamon and nutmeg over the top.
Now sprinkle brown sugar to cover top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice, ginger ale and frozen lemonade; stir well.
Just before serving, slice sherbet into chunks and add to punch.
Stir slightly until sherbet is almost melted and combined. Serves about 25.

title: four-bean hot dish
directions: In a medium skillet, cook bacon and onion until bacon is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
In a 2-quart baking dish, combine the bacon mixture and remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: cobbler batter
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk, then melted butter. Pour into well-buttered large sheet pan.
Pour heated sweetened fruit on top of batter.
Peaches are especially good.
Add bit of butter on fruit.
Bake at 450° until well browned on top, about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry banana pineapple jello salad
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add mashed bananas, pineapple (with juice) and strawberries.
Pour into jello mold.
Let set.

title: broccoli soup #2
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Add salt to taste.
Drain.
Chop cooked broccoli up.
Add cheese and butter into hot broccoli. Stir until melted.
In a small bowl, mix flour, 1 cup milk and pepper until smooth.
Add to broccoli mixture slowly.
Add 3 cups milk slowly.
Bring to a hard simmer.
Serve.

title: my gingerbread boys
directions: Beat sugar and butter until well blended.
Add eggs and molasses.
Stir
in
remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Roll out to
about
1/4-inch
thick and cut out Gingerbread Boys.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix shortening and sugar well. Add eggs and beat well.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Bake about 30 minutes. Don't overbake.

title: baked chicken and ritz
directions: *May use low salt if desired.
Omit salt if used.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water over medium heat until the hard ball stage.
Remove from heat and gradually beat syrup into egg whites.
Beat until the combined mixture loses gloss and hardens. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: pork chop supper
directions: Heat shortening in large skillet or electric frypan.
Brown chops on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add bouillon cube dissolved in water.
Place potatoes on top of chops.
Cover tightly; reduce heat and cook 45 minutes.

title: banbury tarts
directions: Blend two tablespoons butter with 3/4 cups sugar.
Add the juice of one lemon, some grated rind, 2 well beaten egg yolks and one cup of milk.
Stir in 2 well rounded tablespoons flour.
Last fold in two stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for nearly an hour.
Serve cold with whipped cream.
Serves 6, when baked in a pyrex pie dish.

title: dora jean's hot chocolate mix
directions: Use a heaping 1/4 cup mix to 1 cup of hot water.
Makes approximately 50 cups.

title: peruvian lamb chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and oregano; mix well.
Pound flour mixture into lamb chops with the edge of a saucer.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add lamb chops and scallions and cook until chops are browned on both sides.
Arrange chops and scallions in a greased shallow casserole.
Combine coffee and sour cream; blend well.
Pour over lamb chops; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes, or until tender.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Dice apples and nuts. Mix all ingredients well.
Put bananas in last.
Chill and serve.

title: frosted lemon sticks
directions: Sift flour.
Add sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in or knead 1/2 cup margarine.
Add egg, baking soda, sour cream, vanilla and lemon extracts.
Divide dough into 3 sections on a floured board.
Pat into sausage rolls and flatten to about 3 x 14-inch long.
Put jelly, jam or preserves and chopped walnuts down the center.
Fold over and tuck in ends (about 1-inch width). Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Leave in pan for 15 minutes.

title: fat-free pudding
directions: Mix milk and instant pudding and beat until very smooth.
Beat in sour cream until smooth.
Also, beat in half of Cool Whip.
In large container, place layer of graham crackers, layer of pudding and then repeat until pudding is gone, then top with remaining Cool Whip, then chill for 2 hours.

title: creme doodles
directions: Stir Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and honey together, then stir in chocolate, raisins and nuts.
Shape by spoonfuls into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in tightly covered containers.

title: aunt martha's chocolate pretzel rings
directions: Place the pretzels on greased baking sheets. Place a chocolate kiss in the center of each ring. Bake at 275° for 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is softened. Remove from the oven. Place an M&M on each, pressing down slightly so chocolate fills the ring. Refrigerate for 5 to 10 minutes or until chocolate is firm. Store at room temperature. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: frozen natural fruit
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth. Freeze in paper cups or cupcake papers in muffin pan.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt on stove margarine and brown sugar.
Add nuts, coconut and Rice Chex.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread ice cream over and sprinkle reserved cup of Rice Chex over ice cream.
Freeze.

title: danish ham rolls
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine to room temperature.
Blend in flour.
Shape into a ball and place in refrigerator for 4 to 5 hours.
Place on a floured board and roll out to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place in small pieces of ham (cooked) on half of biscuits and fold over, forming a half moon shape.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and drain cucumbers, onions and green peppers.
Put in layers; sprinkle with salt.
Cover with ice for 3 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Add drained cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Bring to a full boil again.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Pack hot in jars.
Seal.

title: creamy cheese ball
directions: Let set until soft enough to make ball, then cover with nuts. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook the butter and brown sugar on low heat 2 minutes. Add the milk and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add sifted powdered sugar until of right consistency.

title: carnation cream caramels
directions: Cook in heavy saucepan until clear and thick or to 250° on a candy thermometer. Add the Carnation milk (take pan off burner), adding a small amount at a time. Stir into hot mixture until milk is all used. Continue cooking, stirring constantly to 240°. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and pour into greased pan to cool. When cold, cut and wrap each piece in waxed paper.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Bake cake mix by directions on box.
Let cool.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour and 1/3 cup sugar; cut in butter.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together eggs, 3/4 cup sugar, lemon juice, flour and baking powder.
Pour over cooled crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar. Mix with pudding mix and milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Crush Oreos until they look like "dirt".
Leave creme centers in.
Layer cookies, then cream mixture, cookies, cream mixture and end with cookies on top.

title: onion-cheese bread
directions: Mix egg, milk, then biscuit mix.
Add onion, half of the cheese and parsley.
Put in an 8-inch round greased pan.
Sprinkle leftover cheese and butter over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Place berries in small casserole dish
and add gelatin.
Place in refrigerator until set.
Mix cream
cheese
and
sour
cream.
Blend in just enough powdered sugar
until slightly sweet.
Spread over set gelatin/berries.
Sprinkle pecans over top.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice; set aside.
Saute onion and celery in the 1/2 stick butter; cook a few minutes on a low fire.
Add cream of chicken soup, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Cook a few
minutes until all blended.
Mix all together with broccoli and rice in casserole pan.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients all together and chill overnight.
Spread with Chicken in a Biskit crackers.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remember to sift flour 3 or 4 times before mixing.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, hot water and cold water or pineapple juice. Chill until partly thickened, then fold in crushed pineapple and cranberry sauce.

title: fiery cajun shrimp
directions: Stir together butter, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, pepper, hot sauce, garlic and salt. Pour half mixture into a large casserole dish. Layer half the shrimp and half the lemon slices in the dish, then form a second layer with the remaining shrimp and lemon slices; pour remaining sauce into the dish. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes or until the shrimp are pink, stirring twice. Pour off the sauce into individual dishes. Serve this dish with a crusty bread for dipping.

title: old south buttermilk pie
directions: Whisk flour and sugar together.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into frozen or very cold pie shell.
Bake about 40 minutes at 375° until lightly browned and firm.
So good and so easy!

title: cranberry punch
directions: Cook until cranberries are soft.
Strain and add sugar; cook 5 minutes.
Add juice of oranges and lemon.
If hot drink is desired, add 1
quart
water
and
heat.
If
cold drink is desired, add 1 quart ginger ale.
Pour over ice.

title: cheddar onion dip
directions: In medium bowl, blend soup mix, sour cream, cheese and pimento.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Serve with chips or cut up raw vegetables.

title: cranberried chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate for 24 hours. Do not drain.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done, spooning glaze over chicken once or twice while baking.
Serve with rice and your favorite veggie.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add shortening, 1/3 cup buttermilk and bananas.
Mix with electric mixer for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add remaining 1/3 cup buttermilk and eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in nuts.

title: turkey broccoli casserole
directions: Cook noodles and broccoli as directed on the packages.
Drain. Melt margarine; stir in flour and seasonings.
Add milk slowly; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat; add cheese and stir until melted.
Dice broccoli stems and leaves; keep flowerets whole.
Place noodles, broccoli stems and turkey in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over ingredients in baking dish.
Arrange broccoli flowerets on top, pressing them into sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings (1 cup size).

title: sweet and savory meat balls
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, garlic and egg.
Shape into small meat balls.
Brown in shortening; pour off excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients except rice.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until meat is done, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Fix jello with one cup hot water.
Add juice of pineapple with water to make 3/4 cup cool liquid to make jello.
Add cream cheese to hot mixture, then cool liquid with other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: waldorf salad dressing(mildred gregory)
directions: Blend ingredients with an egg beater.
This dressing can be used on a mixture of chopped apple and celery with raisins and nuts usually English walnuts.

title: chewy fudge squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir together mix, eggs and butter until well blended (mixture will be stiff). Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: overnight rolls
directions: At 12:00 Noon, boil sugar and 2 cups of water for 5 minutes. Add Crisco and let cool.
Add salt, eggs, yeast dissolved in 1/2 cup of warm water.
Mix with mixer.
Add flour and cover with cloth.
Let rise, about 7 hours.

title: fried green beans
directions: Begin frying bacon; add enough cooking oil to make 1/8 inch deep in skillet.
Add chopped onions.
Cok 2 to 3 minutes.
Add green beans, salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Turn with spatula every 2 to 3 minutes.
Fry until tender or still slightly crunchy.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: date pecan pie
directions: Combine sour cream, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt in a bowl. Mix well.
Add dates and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until filling is set and golden.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple with pudding and add marshmallows, nuts and 1/4 of whipped topping.
Put remaining topping on top and chill 2 hours.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream sugar
and
eggs together.
Mix other ingredients with sugar and eggs.
Bake in oblong pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.

title: curried tuna
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended. Prepare ahead of time to improve flavor. Chill and use as spread on crackers of choice.

title: oven kalna pig
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Rub pork with liquid smoke and 1 1/2 tablespoons of salt.
Wrap with foil.
Place in roasting pan and bake 5 hours.
After baking, shred pork.
Sprinkle with remaining salt.
Serves 12.

title: family casserole
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper until tender.
Brown hamburger meat, salt and pepper to taste.
Combine vegetables and hamburger meat.
Add rice, tomatoes and spices.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place 3 strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pan sauteed onions and pears
directions: Quarter the pears; core and pare, slice lengthwise 1/4-inch thick.
Heat 1 tablespoon of butter, stirring often.
Saute onions until golden brown.
Remove and reserve.

title: coconut buttermilk pie
directions: Mix
all
together
well
and pour in 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix beef, egg and onion.
Shape into patties and brown over high heat, drain off any fat.
Pour in bouillon and simmer uncovered until desired doneness.
Serves 4.

title: perfect cheesecake with blueberry topping(makes 12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly butter a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large mixing bowl, combine cheeses; beat until light and fluffy.
Add sugar; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add cornstarch, lemon juice, vanilla and butter; blend until smooth.
Blend in sour cream. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until center is set.
Turn oven off.
Let cheesecake stand in oven with door closed, for 2 hours.
Cool completely.
Chill 6 hours. Spoon blueberry pie filling on top.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Boil eggs; peel and slice lengthwise.
Add sweet pickle relish, Thousand Island dressing and salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle tops with parsley flakes or paprika.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite size pieces.
(This takes about 2 months.)
Add enough water to make a brown gravy.
Cook over a kerosene fire for about 4 months at 465°.
This serves 3,845.
If more are expected, add the hares only if necessary because most people don't like to find hares in their stew!

title: skillet pork chops and potatoes
directions: Season the pork chops with the salt, pepper and season salt. Brown chops, then add the soup, spooning on top of chops.
Add the water, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Peel the potatoes and slice on top of chops and soup. Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: blanca's bocadillos
directions: Mix well.
