Drop by spoonfuls into heated Mazola oil and fry on both sides until slightly golden.
Drain on paper towels and serve warm or at room temperature.

title: butterhorns
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; shape into balls.
Wrap and chill 2 hours.
Roll in circles.
Cut in wedges.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over; roll.
Bake in ungreased pan at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels with butter in double boiler.
Add pecans and drop on greased cookie sheet and cool.
Melt Hershey bars and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip caramel in chocolate and put on greased cookie sheet.

title: scrambled tofu and tofu rancheros
directions: Heat wok with oil (or skillet).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Fry until tofu starts to turn brown.
Serve with toast or rice.
Yields 3 cups.

title: ed's punch
directions: Mix all liquids.
Slice oranges and limes and add to liquid. Add cherries.
Stir well, then add sherbet.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese by setting out ahead of time or take out of foil and put in microwave for 1 minute.
Mix all ingredients together.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Trim chicken breasts of skin and fat.
Place in large bowl. Pour Italian dressing over top and mix with hands.
Squeeze limes into dressing.
Cover and marinate for 6 to 8 hours.
Grill chicken breasts on outside grill, sprinkling with paprika for color.
When done, cut chicken in strips 1/4-inch wide crossways. Warm tortillas and refried beans.
Place chicken strips in tortilla; doctor with beans, cheese, lettuce, onion, tomato and/or hot sauce.
Roll up and eat with hands.
Watch out for loose ends. Feeds 12 people.

title: granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add honey, oil and vanilla and mix well.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cool and eat.
Great snack for kids!

title: cheese strata
directions: Arrange 6 slices of bread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish. Place cheese, broccoli and ham in layers and top with remaining bread slices.
Combine milk, eggs, onion, salt and mustard; blend well.
Pour over layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Allow to return to room temperature before baking.
Preheat oven to 325° and bake 55 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cheesy salmon loaf
directions: Combine salmon with liquid and dry ingredients.
Put in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter with butter and sugar until smooth.
Form balls and refrigerate (or freeze).
Melt chocolate and paraffin. Using toothpick, dip cold Buckeyes in chocolate until 2/3 covered. Let dry on waxed paper.

title: company pot roast
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large Dutch oven until tender.
Add meat and brown on both sides.
Combine seasonings and diluted consomme. Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, pineapple and juice.
Melt butter and add bread.
When coated with butter and slightly browned, add to the pineapple mixture.
Place in greased quart casserole dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: new quick fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil hen until tender. Boil eggs. Take 1 cup of chicken broth out of pot and let cool until you can mix dumplings. Do not use any shortening or milk, just the broth of the chicken. Roll out dumplings (made with enough flour to reach right consistency) and cut small. Put eggs, onions and dumplings in pot with deboned chicken and broth. Cook about 10 or 15 minutes slowly.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Stir in the rest of ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate to blend flavors. Serve with crisp veggies or crackers.
Or serve in scooped out black bread and use pieces scooped out for dipping.

title: red raspberry cream cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat together softened cream cheese and the whipping cream.
Spread mixture over bottom of the cooled pie shell; chill.
Reserve half of the raspberries.
In a large mixing bowl, mash the remaining raspberries.
Stir in sugar; let stand about 1 hour.
Sieve berry mixture.
In a saucepan, combine pineapple juice and cornstarch; stir in sieved berry mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until berry mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Spread three-fourths of the thickened berry mixture over cream cheese layer in pie shell.
Arrange 1 1/2 cups of the reserved whole berries over top of pie.
Spoon the remaining cooked berry mixture over whole berries.
Chill about 2 hours or until set.
Garnish with whipped cream and reserved fresh raspberries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: janice's lasagna
directions: Cook onion and ground beef until meat loses pink color.
Add next 8 ingredients (whirl tomatoes in blend).
Cook over low heat about 3 hours.
Layer in large casserole 1/2 the noodles, cottage cheese, additional Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sugar together, should have creamy texture.
Mix pineapple, strawberries, bananas, Cool Whip and nuts together.
Mix all the ingredients gently and then freeze.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush cookies in food processor or blender and set aside.
Mix margarine and sugar.
Add cream cheese, pudding mix, milk and Cool Whip and blend well.
Cover bottom of new, plastic, 7-inch flower pot with foil.
Place a layer of pudding on foil.
On this layer place the gummy worms if desired.
Add another layer of pudding and the top layer is the crushed cookies.
Put small bouquet of plastic flowers in middle of dirt pudding.
Keep refrigerated.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onions 5 minutes in salted water. Drain. Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in carrots. Fold this into squash and onions. Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread half of the stuffing mixture in bottom of 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon vegetable mixture on top and sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetables.
Bake at 350° until heated (30 to 40 minutes). Makes 6 servings.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Add snow to desired consistency.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding according to directions on package. Add chocolate cake mix.
Stir.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with chocolate bits and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: ginger orange chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry and place in large, shallow bowl. Combine honey, Worcestershire, ginger, paprika, orange juice and oil, whisking well.
Brush over chicken and marinate, refrigerated, for at least 1 hour, turning once or twice.

title: polish cole slaw
directions: Mix vegetables in a bowl with 1/2 cup of sugar.

title: cube steaks with gravy
directions: Place flour in a large resealable plastic bag.
Add steaks, a few at at time, and shake until completely coated.
In a skillet, cook steaks in oil until lightly browned on each side.
Transfer to a slow cooker.
Add the onion and 2 cups water. Cover and cook on low for eight hours or until meat is tender.
In a bowl, whisk together gravy mixes with remaining water.
Add to slow cooker; cook 30 minutes longer.
Serve over mashed potatoes or noodles. Yields 6 servings.

title: baked fish in mushroom sauce(serves 4 to 5)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Arrange potatoes, zucchini and carrots evenly in bottom of a 12 x 8-inch rectangular baking dish. Combine undiluted soup, wine, scallions and parsley;
mix until blended.
Pour half of soup mixture over vegetables, spreading evenly with a rubber spatula.
Arrange fish in a single layer over all; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Pour remaining soup mixture over fish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake about 25 minutes, or until fish is just opaque throughout.
To serve, use a wide spatula to remove from fish.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat
eggs;
add
sugar,
melted margarine, cornstarch, vanilla,
pecans
and chips.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: cinnamon stars
directions: Mix egg whites, cinnamon and sugar until well blended.
Set aside 1/4 cup for frosting.
Add finely ground almonds.
Roll out mixture on sugar-flour dusted board to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with star cutter, frost with egg mixture stiffened with additional confectioners sugar.
Decorate with sprinkles.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: never fail hollandaise sauce
directions: Divide the butter into 3 parts.
Beat the egg yolks and lemon juice together.
Add 1 piece of butter; cook in a double boiler, stirring constantly, until the mixture begins to thicken.
Remove from stove.
Add a second piece of butter; stir rapidly, then add the remaining butter and continue to stir until the mixture is completely blended.
Add the salt, cayenne and boiling water; return to double boiler and stir until the sauce thickens.

title: beef brisket roast
directions: Put brisket in baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasoned salts and liquid smoke.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, sprinkle with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover baking dish with foil.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Uncover and pour barbecue sauce over meat.
Cook, uncovered, for another hour.
If gravy is desired, remove meat and add flour and water to drippings in baking dish.
This is very good served cold or for sandwiches.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Bring water to a boil and pour over jars filled with small cucumbers that are heated.
Seal and place in some place they may ferment and run over but will be alright.
I never tighten lids after fermenting.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix cheeses together and add milk and egg.
Put a small amount of spaghetti sauce with hamburger in it over the bottom of a large pan.
Stuff the shells with tablespoon of cheese; mix and place in pan, folded side down.
Place all the shells in the pan and cover with the rest of the spaghetti and meat mixed together.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: skillet slaw
directions: Grease a heavy iron skillet. Combine all ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring often, for 10 minutes or until vegetables are hot.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding mix together.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Beat until fluffy.
Put in container and set in refrigerator.
Do not stir anymore.
You can use 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Soften ice cream.
Melt chocolate chips in large pan.
Add peanut butter; melt with chips.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir well. Mix in marshmallows.
Add to ice cream.
Put in a spring-form pan. Freeze overnight.
Break away sides.
Spread Cool Whip over it and garnish with nuts, chocolate chips or your own toppers.

title: chicken-andouille gumbo
directions: Cut up chicken.
Wash and season with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 cup of oil in heavy skillet and fry chicken until brown.
Remove chicken and put aside.
Pour remaining oil into large, heavy pot for making roux.

After roux is made, lower heat and add all chopped ingredients, except green onions, garlic and parsley. Cover and simmer until onions are clear, stirring occasionally. Add sliced andouille and chicken to roux mixture.
Cover and let simmer about 1/2 hour.
Stir often during this process.
Keep heat low through this point.
Add water, garlic, parsley and green onions.
You may increase heat until mixture begins to boil.
Now lower heat to simmer; cover and cook 1 1/2 hours to 2 hours or until chicken is tender.
This has a lot of liquid and is served over rice, over which 1/4 teaspoon file has been sprinkled.
Makes enough rice for 6 people.

title: german spaghetti
directions: Dice up bacon and onion and brown in skillet; pour off excess grease.
Cook tomatoes and little bit of sugar; salt and pepper. Cook spaghetti until done.
Drain.
Add everything to the tomatoes and cook on medium heat until it is done, about 45 minutes.

title: baked clams ala marie
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil in a medium frying pan.
Add all other ingredients when onions and garlic are lightly browned. Take off burner and mix with minced clams.
Put in individual clam shells or in a pie dish and bake at 375°.

title: sauerkraut and spareribs
directions: Place sauerkraut in Dutch oven pan.
Place ribs on top.
Salt and pepper.
Pour water down the side so you won't disturb salt and pepper on ribs. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Very good with mashed taters.

title: to-po pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Lightly grease heavy skillet with fat from one chop.
Brown chops on both sides.
Season each side with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Remove chops; drain fat from skillet.
Add tomatoes to skillet; break up with fork.
Mix in water, 1 teaspoon salt, the basil and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Layer potatoes in tomato mixture.
Arrange onions over potatoes.
Top with chops.
Cover tightly.
Simmer 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender and chops are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight to allow flavors to mingle.
Serve with bite-sized chunks of raw veggies.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Place in bowl in this order:
lettuce, cauliflower, onion, Miracle Whip, Parmesan cheese, sugar and then the Bac*Os.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator overnight or for several hours.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Pour rice into 2-quart dish.
Slice onion and place over rice. Place seasoned chicken over onions.
Mix soup and water and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover for last 5 minutes to brown chicken.

title: party potatoes
directions: Beat softened cream cheese, sour cream and margarine until well blended.
Add hot potatoes, beating until smooth.
Season to taste.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, covered.
This can be fixed early and heated at serving time.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Lightly cook the onions in butter.
Add the potatoes and the water.
Cook until tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Melt the cheese in the milk in the top of a double boiler.
Add the cheese mixture to the potato-onion-water mixture.
Add the cooked shrimp; heat.
This soup can be re-warmed nicely.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Pick chicken off the bones and then add the ingredients to it. Simmer for a few minutes. Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: low-fat eggplant parmesan
directions: Slice eggplant and place in a tray style pan.
Spray pan with olive oil spray.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Turn.
Bake for 10 more minutes.

title: crabbies
directions: Split muffins. Melt butter and cheese. Stir in seasonings. Add crabmeat which has been drained and picked. Spread on muffins. Cut each half into eighths. Put under broiler until cheese melts or bubbles.

title: yummy banana pudding
directions: Mix together three small boxes instant pudding and five cups cold
milk.
Fold
in
tub Cool Whip and sour cream. Layer vanilla
wafers,
bananas
and pudding mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top.
Seal and refrigerate.

title: pasta salad
directions: Add rainbow shells to 6 cups boiling water.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes or until tender.
Drain and rinse.
Add 6 ounces mushroom salad.
Pour 12 ounce bottle of Italian dressing over cooked shells.
Toss together.
Add other vegetables, cheese and pepperoni as desired.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add nuts, cherries and dates, also the mixed fruits.
Chill at least one hour.
Drop by teaspoons about 2-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake about 8 minutes at 400°.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Sprinkle drained, cooked sausage in casserole dish; put layer of bread cubes, next layer of meat and then Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk and other ingredients.
Pour this mixture over the layer.
Cover and place refrigerator overnight.
Remove and allow to stand until room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: garlic cheese apples
directions: Grind the first 5 ingredients together.
Mix thoroughly with hands after sprinkling with the vinegar and a pinch of salt. Shape into apples or rolls.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika; let stand 2 hours before refrigerating.
Refrigerate.
Cut into slices; serve with crackers.

title: andrew's fudgies
directions: Blend the 2/3 cup oil and cocoa.
Add the additional oil and eggs, then the sugar, flour, baking soda, vanilla and cold water. You will think it is a big mistake, but keep blending until you have a smooth batter.
Pour
into a non-greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Sprinkle the nuts and morsels on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.
Enjoy!

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl in order, using lettuce and greens to fill at least half the bowl.
Save a few of the peas to scatter on top as a garnish for color.
Generally, this salad should be made one day ahead and covered with plastic wrap to allow the flavors to blend.
When serving, be certain to dig to the bottom of the bowl with each spoonful.

title: patricia's blonde brownies(southern accent cookbook)
directions: Mix well the butter, flour, sugar and soda.
Beat in eggs; add vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool; cut into squares.
Yields 24.

title: carrots supreme
directions: Cook carrots for 8 minutes; drain.
Place in 1-quart baking dish.
Stir in raisins, butter, honey, lemon juice and ginger. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: cranberry-glazed pork roast
directions: In small saucepan, stir together all ingredients except pork. Cook, stirring, over medium heat, until thickened.
Set aside.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute the onion in the butter in a medium saucepan over medium-low heat; do not brown onion.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling; lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Refrigerate the cooled barbecue sauce in tightly covered containers for up to 2 weeks.

title: banana split cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions, except substitute milk for water.
Boil together the sugar and pineapple while cake is baking.
After cake is done, punch hole in cake and pour pineapple mixture over.
Let it set a while.

title: favorite apple pie
directions: Peel and cut all apples.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix everything until well mixed.
Place in your 9 x 13-inch deep dish cake pan or into two 9-inch glass pie pans.
Dot with 1 quarter margarine.
Cover pie filling with top.
Sprinkle and coat top with canned whole milk.
Sprinkle milk with just table sugar. Bake in 425° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add egg; mix well.
Spread sliced apples in baking pan and cover with mixture.
Sprinkle with spices and 2 more tablespoons of sugar.
Dot with butter, then sprinkle water over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cook a few minutes longer, if needed.

title: raspberry tang salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; set aside to cool.
Cream cheese by adding a little mayonnaise at a time.
Add pineapple, banana, coconut and pecans.
When jello just begins to set, add cheese and fruit mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and congeal.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Makes 10 servings.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
With floured hands, roll into balls.
Smash them with a fork.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes.

title: "you can do it" cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix filling ingredients together. Open can of rolls, separating dough into 4 rectangles. Press the diagonal indentations together in each rectangle. Put about 1 tablespoon filling on each rectangle, spreading it from one end, leaving a little space in the other end, as the filling will spread more as you roll it up. Roll up from the short end like a pinwheel. Repeat with all of the rectangles. Slice each rolled up rectangle into 3 pieces, placing in lightly greased 9-inch cake or pie pan. One can will fill up one cake pan with 12 small rolls. Bake for approximately 18 minutes in a 350° oven. (If you do not need 24 rolls, just open one can and save the remaining filling for another time.)
Cool slightly, then drizzle with this mixture: 2/3 cup powdered sugar, sifted, and 1 tablespoon milk, stirred together.

title: chocolate whipped cream angel food cake
directions: Whip first four ingredients until it stands in peaks.
Split angel food cake into three layers.
Spread each layer with whipped cream mix and sprinkle with some of the crushed Heath bars. Spread whipped cream mixture on top and down sides.
Sprinkle with Heath bar.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Use blender.
Combine all ingredients; process until smooth. Makes 1 can or 1 1/4 cups.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage; cook and drain.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with crescent rolls.
Press seams together and press slightly up around edges of pan.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese. Combine other ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: diet chicken and broccoli stir-fry
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute garlic and vegetables in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes or until done.
Serve over brown rice.

title: tomato beef stew
directions: Roll meat in flour; brown in shortening in a large heavy pan. Add soup and water; cover.
Simmer 1/2 hour; stir now and then. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook until the vegetables are tender, about 1 hour.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add vanilla.
Stir in eggs, 1 at a time.
Stir in flour; add nuts if desired and mix well.
(All done in a large mixing bowl).
Spread 3/4 of the batter in 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking pan.
Top with the pie filling and spread remaining batter over the top (in swirls, will not cover completely).
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Cool, then sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: cool fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together all ingredients, except bananas and Cool Whip.
Chill for 1 hour.
Just before serving, add bananas and top with Cool Whip.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Fry the bacon; remove from pan.
Add the onion, bell pepper, celery, tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar and hot sauce to the grease. Cook for 1 hour, then add the shrimp.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serve with salad and rolls.

title: bread appetizer
directions: Remove crusts from bread and roll each piece with a rolling pin.
Combine cream cheese, egg yolks and sugar together.
Spread mixture on bread; roll.
Dip in melted butter.
Roll in brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in half.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Stack in freezer container, after they are frozen, with wax paper in between.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
It will mix better if slightly warm macaroni, not hot (will melt cheese).
Serve individually, on lettuce leaf, or family style.

title: meat loaf(ultra low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Place in loaf pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove and serve.
Great with a baked potato or cold on a sandwich.
Makes 8 servings.
Per serving: 2 grams of fat and 143 calories.

title: brisket
directions: Trim most of fat off brisket.
Put foil in pan with sides high enough to seal brisket in.
Put brisket in pan.
Pour brisket sauce on and seal.
Marinate at least 3 or 4 hours in refrigerator.
Put in oven and cook until tender at 275°.
Usually takes 8 or 9 hours.
About 30 minutes before done, uncover and let brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, egg, yolk and vanilla. Add dry ingredients. Stir in chips. Use 1/4 cup of dough to drop on cookie sheet. I cover sheets with foil to prevent browning and easier cleanup. Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes (16). Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Fry bacon.
Chop pepper and onion; saute in bacon grease until tender.
Pour up grease, except enough to scramble eggs in.
After scrambling eggs, chop eggs into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients with cooked rice in a large pan; add soy sauce to taste.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Drain cucumber well.
Combine cream cheese and cucumber; mix well.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Serve with potato chips or as a dip.

title: eric's special c.c. cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add vanilla pudding mix; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream together shortening and margarine.
Add sugars.
Blend thoroughly.
Add vanilla flavor and eggs; mix well until smooth.
Gradually add flour mixture 1/4 at a time, mix well after each addition.
Stir in chips.
Refrigerate dough at least 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream the butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt; blend into the creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hobos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pat out hamburger in a large patty. Slice peeled potato and place on hamburger patty.
Peel and slice carrots; place on potato.
Peel and slice onion and place on carrots.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Wrap in aluminum foil, fold loosely over Hobo and place in pan.
Put in oven.
Bake for about 1 hour on 350°.
Yields 1 Hobo.

title: whiskey slushes
directions: Add tea bags to boiling water.
Brew until dark.
Remove tea bags.
Pour into large container that can go into freezer.
Add other ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Place in freezer.

title: pesticide
directions: Coarsely chop garlic, peppers and onion.
Puree in blender. Add mixture to water and let steep overnight.
Strain and add a few drops of dish liquid.
(The soap helps the solution stick to the plants' leaves and stems.)
Use as needed.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts last.
Best served with sliced apples.

title: icebox pie
directions: Layer a 9 x 9-inch pan with 9 of the graham crackers.
Mix vanilla sugar-free pudding according to the package.
Pour over the graham crackers.
Layer the vanilla pudding with the remaining 9 graham crackers.
Mix chocolate sugar-free pudding according to the package and pour over the graham crackers.
Top with light Cool Whip.
Let set in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Serves 9.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Add hot water to raisins; cool.
Add mashed potatoes, oil and honey.
Mix with corn meal, baking powder and oats.
Fill greased muffin tin 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: poached chicken in basil wine
directions: Wash and dry chicken; saute carrot and onion in butter; put in crock-pot.
Brown fryer in fry pan and put in crock.
Add wine, leaf, stock, basil, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Remove chicken, keep warm, pour juice in saucepan.
Skim fat, boil down to 1 cup.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Melt sugar, butter and syrup.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes. Do not stir for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over 6 quarts popped popcorn and stir. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: bill's baking powder biscuits
directions: Oven temperature 450°.
Yield:
12 high or 24 small biscuits.

title: magi bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients, then bananas.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased pans.
Sprinkle top with cherries and slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in 4 mini loaves.
Excellent for Christmas gifts.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise with cream cheese; mix well.
Add fruit, which has been drained.
Add 1 cup of drained juice to mixture.
Also add green and red cherries, if you like, for color.
Freeze.

title: spicy tomato mini-loaves
directions: Thoroughly combine Kellogg's Corn Flakes cereal, 1/2 cup of the Campbell's condensed tomato soup, onion, egg and horseradish.
Mix in ground beef.
Portion meat mixture into 6 parts.
Shape into individual loaves or ovals.
Place on foil-lined baking sheet.
Mix together remaining soup, brown sugar and mustard.
Spread evenly over meat.	Bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes or until meat is cooked.
Serve garnished with parsley, if desired.	Yield:	6 servings.

title: quickest jello salad ever!
directions: In large bowl, add jello to cottage cheese.
Mix well until jello is thoroughly dissolved.
Add Cool Whip; stir well.
Add berries; stir well.
Garnish with remaining berries.

title: corn bread sausage stuffing
directions: In large skillet, cook mushrooms, celery and onions in margarine until tender.
Add water and bouillon.
Cook until bouillon dissolves.
In large bowl combine mushroom mixture and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Loosely stuff turkey just before roasting, if desired.
Place remaining stuffing in greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chopped ham with mushrooms and egg
directions: Cut ham into strips, 1 1/4 x 1/4-inches.
Heat ham strips and drained mushrooms in skillet; stir in onion salt.
Spread ham mixture evenly over bottom of skillet.
Break eggs on top of ham; season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook, without stirring, until eggs are done.
Yields 4 servings.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine
veggies,
soup,
half of the
cheese
and
sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can French
fried onions.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.

title: macaroni tuna salad
directions: Stir lemon juice into Carnation milk until milk thickens.
Add salad dressing, pepper and mustard; mix well.
Combine salad dressing and remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Toss lightly; chill.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Bake 2 layers; cut in 1/2 to make 4 layers.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar together to use as the first layer mix.
Mix sugar and blueberry filling together to use as the second layer.
Spread layer mixes on top of cake layers.
Mix the 2 leftover mixes together; spread on cake to cover.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Work shortening into dry ingredients (flour, sugar and salt). Add well beaten egg, vinegar and water.
Mix lightly.
Makes 2 covered pies.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Wash cukes; slice lengthwise and remove seeds.
Do not cut off skin.
Put through food chopper (small grind; I use a Cuisinart). Put in crock or stainless; sprinkle 1/2 cup pickling salt.
Let stand overnight (or a few hours), covered, then drain.
Mix all dry ingredients, except sugar.
Put 3/4 of the vinegar in an enamel or stainless (not aluminum) kettle.
Add sugar; bring to boil.
Add 1/4 cup vinegar to spices; mix to paste.
Add to hot vinegar; mix well.
Add relish to vinegar; simmer for 20 minutes. Jar and seal.
Store when cool.

title: applesauce-spice cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; blend, then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut the elephant into small bite size pieces.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook for 4 weeks at 425°.
Will feed up to 2,500 people.
If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added.
Do this only in an emergency, most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Using wooden spoon handle, poke holes in cake.
Pour hot fudge sauce over cake and cool thoroughly.
Cover with large container of Cool Whip. May sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Refrigerate.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute the hamburger until it is separated into pieces about the size of pecans and slightly browned.
Then combine it and all the other ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
The noodles are put into this mixture just as they come from the package, no precooking.

title: maxine's dilemma
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Press in pan and bake at 350° for 10 or 12 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt in mixing bowl. Beat butter, shortening, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy. Beat in flour mixture.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
In a separate pan mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add broccoli and mixture in a baking dish and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cherry walnut squares(very special)
directions: Heat margarine until melted.
Add next 5 ingredients and blend well.
Reserve 3/4 cup crumb mixture.
Press remainder in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Spread over hot baked layer and bake for 20 minutes. Spread cherry pie filling over cheese layer.

title: pasta with bechamel sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, heat milk and bay leaf over low heat to just below boiling point.
Remove from heat.
Discard bay leaf. In a small saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in flour. Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in hot milk.
Return to pan to heat.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Reduce heat to low and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Season with salt and pepper.
(If sauce is not to be used immediately, cover with plastic wrap.)
Serves 4.

title: blumenkohl (vegetable dip)
directions: Mix sugar and oil until sugar is dissolved.
Add mayonnaise and stir.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: hot polish potato salad
directions: Cut kielbasa in half lengthwise, then slice it in about 1/4 to 1/3-inch pieces.
Brown lightly in 2 tablespoons oil.
Clean and halve the potatoes, then slice them into about 1/4 to 1/3-inch pieces (like the meat).
Peel and dice onion.
Mince garlic cloves.
Combine potatoes, onion and garlic; brown in remaining 2 tablespoons oil.
Combine meat and vegetables.
Add water, vinegar, sugar and spices (to include salt).
Bring to a slow boil; boil for 5 to 10 minutes.
Turn heat down; simmer for 35 to 45 minutes, or until potatoes are done.
Serve hot or cold. Serves 4 to 5.

title: congealed salad
directions: 1. Mix all ingredients in bowl and refrigerate.
2. Serve as salad or dessert.

title: rinke rhubarb
directions: In an enamel or Pyrex saucepan, put in 1/2 cup of cold water and 1 cup of sugar.
Boil until a syrup is formed.
Add spices, lemon and rhubarb (which will foam on continued boiling).
Put aside to simmer.
Taste for any needed additional sweetening after first adding applesauce.

title: surprise cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine until softened.
Add brown sugar and sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and extract and beat well.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Gradually add flour mixture to margarine, beating until well mixed.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips, chopped cherries and coconut.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute.
Remove cookies to rack to cool.
Makes about 36 cookies.

title: double fudge brownies
directions: Melt butter, then add sugar and vanilla.
Pour in a mixing bowl and blend in eggs.
Next, add the flour, cocoa and baking powder; mix well.
Finally, mix in chocolate chips.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar and oil until sugar dissolves.
Let cool completely before pouring.
Refrigerate overnight and the vegetables will be ready to serve the next day.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, combine oats and milk.
Set aside until milk is absorbed.
In medium bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Add butter, egg and bananas to oat mixture, then add to dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Stir in sunflower seeds.
Fill greased 2 1/2-inch muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes or until testing done.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: ain't it great cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl; add liquids and stir just enough for all ingredients to be wet.
Pour into buttered and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan before removing.
Cake becomes moist with age.
Tastes best when 2 or 3 days old.

title: peanut butter yummies
directions: Put the butterscotch chips in the saucepan and melt slowly over low heat.
When melted, stir in peanut butter, one spoonful at a time.
Take the pot off the heat and stir in the cornflakes. Take your spoon and carefully place spoonfuls on a cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Place in your refrigerator until firm. Serve cold.

title: low-fat fettuccine
directions: Cook pasta; drain
and	return	to pan.
Add olive oil, toss to coat,
add
milk,
1/3 cup cheese, onion, basil, lemon peel, garlic
powder
and
pepper.
Cook over medium-high heat until bubbly,
stirring constantly.
Season.
Top with cheese and basil. Serve with lemon.	Makes 6 side dishes.

title: trail mix magic
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss well.
Store in a tightly covered container.
You can also add almonds, filberts, pecans, dried figs, apples, peaches, pears, dates, sesame seed, candied pineapple, chocolate or carob chips.

title: strawberries in swedish cream
directions: Mix cream and sugar in a pan.
Heat gently.
When sugar dissolves, add gelatin.
Stir over very low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Do not boil.
Cool slightly until it begins to thicken.
When cool, fold in sour cream.
Flavor with vanilla. Chill until firm.
Serve on top of berries.

title: layered pudding cake
directions: Make cake as per directions.
Cool.
Make pudding and cool. Spread pudding layer over cake.
Top with chocolate Cool Whip and refrigerate.
Cut and serve.

title: baked ham
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Place ham, fat side up, uncovered, no water.
Bake 4 to 5 hours.
Mix together brown sugar, flour and mustard for glaze.
Increase heat to 400°.
Spread glaze over ham and bake for 20 minutes.

title: chicken in a wok (stir-fry)
directions: Mix the chicken with the ginger, salt and paprika.
Heat the oil in wok and saute the chicken for approximately 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Push the chicken aside.
Add vegetables and cook for about 5 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
Add the broth and the soy sauce.
Cover and cook on low heat for another 5 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch, cook until the sauce thickens slightly and serve.
I like to serve over rice or chow mein noodles.
I also like to add vegetables and sliced water chestnuts.

title: egg salad-cheese spread
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a mixing bowl; season with salt and pepper.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt, soda and flour.
Add fruit gently, so as not to loose identity of the fruit.
Pour into greased, floured pan.
Top with brown sugar and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add enchilada sauce.
Layer chips, meat and cheese in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: bacon cookies
directions: Wrap 1 strip of bacon around soda cracker.
Place in pan and cook until bacon is done and crispy.

title: crazy meat balls
directions: Sauce:
Mix sauerkraut, cranberry sauce, chili sauce, water and brown sugar.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 3/4-inch slices.
Do not peel.
Dip in seasoned flour.
Fry on both sides in hot shortening until crisp and golden.

title: date bar cookies
directions: First prepare filling and cool.
Mix together in saucepan all ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened (about 10 minutes).
Cool.

title: pickled beets and eggs
directions: Combine beet juice, vinegar, sugar, salt, cloves and cinnamon in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Put eggs and beets in container with a lid.
Pour hot mixture over eggs and beets.
Add a little water, if needed, to cover eggs.
Cover and store in refrigerator a day or two, occasionally shaking container, so eggs color evenly.

title: pumpkin cheesecake squares
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, 1/2 cup nuts and margarine until crumbly.
Stir in 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla; mix well.
Press into bottom of 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked sweet potatoes with equal
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in casserole dish.
Add Equal, butter, nutmeg and water.
Bake until potatoes are done.
Baste regular.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown the meat and drain the fat.
Add the sauce and cook until hot.
Boil noodles according to package directions and then drain. In bowl add all cheeses and noodles until gooey.
Preheat oven for 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover bottom with a little sauce, then layer noodles and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix the last 3 ingredients in large kettle and melt over medium heat.
Mix in the 7 c. of cereal an stir until well mixed. Then add the box of confectionary sugar and stir until coated with the sugar.
Will keep in airtight container.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients until fluffy; gradually add dry, then oats and raisins.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drop by large tablespoon; press down with fingers.
Bake 9 minutes.
Let cool on rack a few minutes before removing.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain off grease.
Mix with softened cream cheese.
Stir in picante sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve hot with chips.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients except flour and chocolate chips in large mixing bowl.
Add flour one cup at a time.
Add chips. Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple dumplings
directions: Melt butter in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish. Set aside. Cook granulated sugar and 1/4 cup water in a saucepan over medium heat until sugar melts. Set aside.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Drain water off potatoes; cream as for mashed potatoes. Peel and drop eggs in potatoes. Add mustard and mayonnaise. Salt to taste. With potato masher, mash all together, then add green onions (chopped). Mix; let cool and refrigerate.

title: stuffed sole
directions: Cut fillet into 6 pieces. Mix melted butter with remaining ingredients. Divide between fillets and roll up.
Secure with toothpick.
Put into baking dish. Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Set aside.
Mix bread crumbs, grated cheese and garlic salt.
Dip veal steaks in flour then quickly in egg mixture.
Dip in bread crumb mixture until well coated. Heat oil in skillet.
Add breaded veal.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Add more oil if necessary.
Drain on paper towel.

title: jail house chili(good)
directions: Fry suet in a heavy kettle or skillet. Add meat, garlic and other seasonings. Cover and cook 4 hours over low heat, stirring occasionally. Add water to desired texture. Cook 1 hour more.

title: lizzies
directions: Combine raisins and bourbon in bowl.
Let stand for 1 hour. Cream margarine and brown sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in raisins with liquid, pecans and cherries.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Store in airtight container. Yield: 10 dozen.

title: aunt joan's baked stew
directions: Place first 7 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in order listed.
Heat soups and wine in saucepan.
Pour over goodies in baking dish.
Sprinkle with parsley, thyme, salt and pepper. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: three pound fruit cake(by bethel lindsey)
directions: Preheat
oven
to
A pan of water placed in oven adds moisture
to
the cake.
Cream butter, add sugar beating well. Add eggs and mix.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternating
with water
or
juice, beating well after each addition. (Hold
in reserve
cup flour for dredging fruit and nuts before	adding to mixture.) Fold in fruit, nuts and molasses. Mix
well.	Pour into
9-inch loaf or tube pan which has been greased
and
lined with
wax paper.
Bake at 275° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil; add flour.
Stir hard. Take off stove; add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water.
Cream together oleo, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, beaten well.
Add cinnamon, salt, soda and flour.
Bake in greased pan at 350°.
When it is baked put the following topping on the cake and place in oven until it bubbles.

title: mama's pecan pie
directions: Mix the brown sugar and white sugar together.
Add the flour, eggs, milk, butter, flavoring and chopped pecans.
Mix very well. Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Makes 2 pies.

title: seafood gumbo(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic in olive oil or bacon fat until soft. Add okra and continue to cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring often. In separate dry pan, cook flour over medium heat. Stirring often, heat until lightly browned (watch it as it burns easily).
When browned, stir this flour into 1/2 cup of water until blended.**
Add tomatoes to sauteed vegetables, then stir in flour mixture. Stir until smooth, then add
crab, shrimp, spices and remaining water or stock.
You can add more stock or water if needed to keep it a soupy consistency. Cover and stir occasionally for about 45 minutes, tasting for spices or salt if needed.
SERVE IN BOWLS OVER FRESH HOT RICE.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients up until it gets like a bread dough; roll out on powdered sugar.
Spread peanut butter on and roll into a log and cut into slices.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Place ginger, garlic, sugar and soy sauce into blender and blend.
Cut the chicken into serving size pieces.
Marinate overnight.
Place marinade and chicken in an ovenproof casserole dish and bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Thaw berries slightly.
Add strawberries, bananas, drained pineapple and nuts.
Place half mixture in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream evenly over top.
Carefully spoon on remaining strawberry mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain grease.
Add mushrooms, soup, and milk; mix and simmer for 10 minutes.
Layer into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add green beans on top of hamburger mix.
Slice Velveeta and layer on top of green beans.
Layer Tater Tots on top of cheese till top is covered.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until Tater Tots are brown.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Beat all ingredients together and freeze.

title: best ever rice casserole
directions: Butter casserole; add rice, butter, soup, water, mushrooms and liquid.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Stir occasionally.

title: eggless buttermilk sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness and cut any desired shape. Sprinkle with a little sugar. Bake about 10 minutes at 400°.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and pack in gallon jar.
Mix plain salt in enough water to cover cucumbers.
Let set 4 days.
Wash 3 times. Mix powdered alum with enough water to cover cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Wash 3 times again.
Drain and put back into jar. Cover with white vinegar for 10 days.
Pour off vinegar.
Add 3 cups of sugar a day for 3 days.
Add pickling spice.
Can or leave in gallon jar.

title: breakfast overnight
directions: Saute meat and drain excess fat.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings.
Layer bread cubes, meat and cheese in a 6 x 8-inch shallow pan.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate overnight covered with foil.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick chili that's good
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
In a large pot, add all ingredients and cook over medium-low heat for at least 30 minutes. Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over chili. Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal honey cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Spray baking pan lightly with cooking spray or grease lightly with butter flavored shortening.

title: broccoli and almond pasta salad
directions: Combine vegetable oil, vinegar, sesame oil and garlic in jar with tight-fitting lid and shake well.
Pour over pasta in large bowl.
Add broccoli, peas, almonds and green onion and toss.
Add cheese and toss again.
Serve salad at room temperature.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: butter meltaways
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, oil and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and cream of tartar; gradually add to the creamed mixture.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in flour; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: ho bo burger
directions: In a large casserole dish, layer all ingredients starting with hamburger.
Press firmly into bottom of dish.
Follow with cabbage, potatoes, onions, carrots, salt and pepper.
After each layer, drop pats of butter between middle and top.
Bake 45 to 65 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and flour.
Add corn and milk. Thoroughly blend.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Store in an airtight container. Use 2 teaspoons in a cup of hot water.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine.
Brown onion and hamburg. Stir in flour, garlic powder, salt, pepper and drained mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup, then return to heat.
Bring to simmer, then cook, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and mix thoroughly.
Heat well without letting it boil.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: poor man's fruit cake
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes or until raisins are done; let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into shallow pan and bake 1 hour in slow oven at 325°.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes.
Drain off juice and add diced onion.
Beat eggs.
Add to potatoes.
Add baking powder, flour and salt.
Mix. Fry on hot griddle until brown on both sides.
Can freeze.

title: heath cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil. Place crackers side by side on it.
Boil oleo and brown sugar 1 minute.
Pour this evenly over crackers.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Take from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over.
The chips will melt; spread chocolate evenly over all.
Chill and break into pieces.

title: carrot ring
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into a buttered ring mold and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Unmold and fill with seasoned peas.
Serves 6.

title: wassail
directions: Simmer all ingredients for at least 20 minutes.
Serve as a holiday drink or to soothe the common cold.

title: potatoes with parsnips and caramelized onions
directions: Melt 1 1/2 tablespoons butter in skillet; add onions and saute until golden (15 minutes).
Mix in rosemary; remove from heat and cover.
Cook potatoes and parsnips for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain well.
Mash vegetables; add butter, then the milk gradually.
Stir in onion
mixture; season with salt and pepper.

title: steak fingers
directions: Cut round steak into 1/2-inch strips.
Mix eggs and milk together in a medium size bowl.
Add steak and let set approximately 30 minutes.
Drain meat and add flour.
Put a lid on bowl and shake until meat is well coated.
Heat the oil in skillet on medium heat and fry steak fingers until golden brown.
Make sauce by blending together the ketchup and horseradish and chill. The fingers are best when dipped in sauce.
They can be served hot or cold.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: shrimp and crab dip
directions: Blend mayonnaise, cream cheese and cottage cheese and add remaining ingredients.
Blend all ingredients well.
Serve with crackers.
Very low-fat.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Uncover; simmer an additional 30 minutes.
Strain spices from mixture.
Yields approximately 11 cups.
This is delicious!

title: peanut pie
directions: Beat
eggs.
Add
sugar
and
syrup,
then add salt and vanilla;
add
margarine last.
Place the peanuts on bottom of uncooked
9-inch pie crust.
Pour filling and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
The nuts rise to the top of filling to form a crusted layer.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Heat together milk, salt, honey and butter until tiny bubbles begin to form around edge.
Cool.
In a large bowl, mix the yeast and lukewarm water.

Add the milk mixture and stir. Add the whole wheat flour and stir. Stir in enough white flour to make a stiff dough that begins to leave the sides of the bowl as you stir. Turn onto a well floured board or oil cloth and knead until dough no longer sticks to your hands.
Add additional flour as you knead to prevent sticking.
Knead until dough springs back when pressed. Place in greased bowl and turn so that all surfaces are greased. Cover with clean cloth and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 45 minutes.

title: chicken dish
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Pull meat from bones.
Put in 13 x 7-inch Pyrex dish.
Melt butter and pour over chicken.
Sift flour, salt, pepper and baking powder.
Blend in milk until smooth.
Spread over chicken.
In pan, blend soup and broth, and heat to boiling point.
Pour over flour mix.
Bake at 400° until brown (approximately 1 hour).

title: pepperoni casserole
directions: Cook shells and drain.
Brown meat and add parsley and garlic powder to taste.
Add sauce, tomato sauce, mushrooms, pepperoni and cheese to shells.
Put cheese and pepperoni on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: orange party salad
directions: Drain pineapple and orange sections.
Add enough water to make 2 cups.
Heat to boiling and pour over gelatin.
Add cream cheese and marshmallows to hot mixture; stir until melted.
Cool.
Add pineapple and orange sections.
Place in refrigerator.
When it is completely cold, add whipped cream.
Dissolve sugar in the whipped cream.
Pour into mold or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at least 60 minutes at 350°.
This is a family favorite, great with coffee, great toasted.

title: red pepper jam
directions: Chop peppers fine (you may use blender).
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 3 to 4 hours. Rinse well and cover with sugar and vinegar.
Boil slowly until thick, stirring often.
Makes 4 to 5 glasses.
Using Certo makes it easier and faster.
You may use food coloring to add desired color.

title: pea and peanut salad
directions: Combine and toss all ingredients in a large bowl until well mixed.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix well.
Add oil and mix well.
Add oats, cornflakes, coconut, pecans and vanilla; stir well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Form into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet 10 minutes before removing.
Makes about 9 1/2 dozen.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta; run under cold water.
Chill.
Mix with red pepper, broccoli and onion.
Add tuna and cheese.
Mix well. Dressing to be added no more than 3 hours prior to serving.
Serve well chilled.

title: seven bean crock-pot meal
directions: Add
chili
beans
and
pork and beans in sauce;
drain liquid from
the rest.
Put all ingredients in a large crock-pot on high heat.
Let boil 1 hour or more;
turn to low until ready to serve.

title: dip
directions: Mix well until smooth.
Serve with crackers, chips, etc.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix in your mixer on medium speed until thick and creamy. Store in jars and you may keep it in the refrigerator until you use it.

title: lipton onion potatoes
directions: In a gallon Ziploc bag, combine Lipton onion soup mix and oil. Mix thoroughly.
Add potatoes.
Zip bag and coat potatoes.
Take out of bag and put in a dish with top and bake in oven, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sour cream, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in oranges, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into container and let congeal in refrigerator.
Makes 15 servings.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: In large salad bowl or deep serving dish, mix well oil, vinegar, salt, oregano and basil.
Add pasta, chickpeas, cherry tomatoes, Mozzarella, salami and olives; toss to combine.
Cover; chill several hours or overnight.
Toss; let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.
Can be made up to a day ahead.

title: wild rice and chicken in a pot
directions: Boil chicken in water until tender; remove chicken and debone. Also remove any skin.
Return meat to broth.
Pour in rice and spices; cook until rice is tender, 25 minutes (covered).
Serve hot.

title: luscious chocolate squares
directions: Combine flour, margarine and 1/2 cup pecans.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in a Dutch oven.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk, half and half and chicken broth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until the mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt, garlic powder and basil.
Add broccoli, then cover and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes or until broccoli is tender.

title: chip-tuna casserole
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Slowly bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add the finely minced onion, salt and pepper.
Arrange in a well buttered casserole. Add the crushed chips (if you are using the tuna, add it also at this time).
Pour the cream soup over all. Bake in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes or until bubbly and slightly browned.

title: moroccan snapper in parchment(serves 2)
directions: Stem and seed peppers; cut into very thin strips.
Slice green onion in diagonal slices.
Slice lemon into 6 slices.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and reserve chunks and juice separately.
In a medium saucepan, cook sugar, egg yolks, flour and pineapple juice over medium heat until mixture is thickened and coats a spoon.
Remove from heat and add margarine.
Stir until blended.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, in large bowl, mix pineapple, apples, marshmallows, cherries, pecans and coconut.
Fold in refrigerated sauce.
Just before serving add container of whipped topping.
Yields 15 to 20 (2/3 cup) servings.

title: barbecues
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain excess liquid.
Place ground beef in crock-pot and add other ingredients.
Let simmer 6 hours.
Serve on buns.
Can freeze.

title: mushroom appetizers
directions: Flatten bread with rolling pin. In small bowl, combine balance of ingredients. Spread with a sixth of the mixture on each slice of bread. Roll up tight like a jelly roll, then roll each one tightly in foil and refrigerate for 2 hours. Slice each roll into 4 pieces. Place on a lightly greased baking sheet seam side down. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly browned. Serve hot or cold. Makes 24 appetizers.

title: ginger-cinnamon tea
directions: In a saucepan, simmer ginger, cinnamon sticks and water for 20 minutes, longer for stronger tea. Add honey or brown sugar and strain tea through sieve.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into cakes and fry in hot oil.

title: dunkin donuts
directions: You will need a frying pan, 3 paper bags, doughnut cutter and a Mom.

Place biscuit on wax paper. Press into round shape. Cut a hole in the center. Put doughnut and "hole" into hot Criso or oil in fry pan and cook until brown. Put sugar in one bag, cinnamon and sugar into another bag and powdered sugar in third bag. Put cooked doughnut in a bag and shake until covered.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat, onions and peppers until brown.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese while hot.

title: three day coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in two 9-inch layers to directions on box. Let cool. Split the two layers into four layers.
Ice each layer. Put in cake and cover or wrap in foil.
Keep covered 3 days in refrigerator before cutting.

title: peanut almond butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Gather all ingredients and sift flour onto waxed paper.
Measure 1 1/2 cups.
Add soda and salt to flour; sift again.
Put egg and softened shortening together.
Add brown sugar and white sugar; mix well.
Stir in peanut butter or almond butter.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture, a bit at a time.
Form dough in small balls with your hands.
Flatten balls by making a crisscross with a fork.
Bake about 10 minutes.

title: bahama punch
directions: Pour all ingredients in a gallon-size container.
Fill with water.
Shake well.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve over ice.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Blend sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and flour gradually and other dry ingredients, stirring thoroughly.
Fold in nuts and peeled, chopped apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in tube pan or until knife comes out clean.

title: texas hash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and bell pepper until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder and pepper. Heat thoroughly.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 60 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk, lemonade and cool whip together.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: pelican white chili
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer.
Serve over cooked rice. Top with sour cream, salsa and grated monterey jack cheese.

title: liver nips
directions: Boil liver, stew meat in enough water to cover well until tender.
Remove liver to medium bow, mash with a fork.
Add flour. onion, salt, and basil, mix well with enough cold water to make a soft dough.
Drop by tsp. into pot of boiling broth with stew beef.
Cook uncovered on medium heat about 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: minute-boil fudge frosting
directions: Place chocolate, sugar, milk, Crisco, butter, corn syrup and salt in saucepan. Bring slowly to a full boil, stirring constantly, and boil briskly for 1 minute. Cool to lukewarm. Add vanilla. Beat until thick enough to spread.
If it gets too thick, add some cream or soften over hot water. Makes enough for 2 (8-inch) layers.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first five ingredients.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Roll into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Blend together and press even in a pie pan.
Bake in a moderate oven.

title: lydia's chicken with coconut milk
directions: Saute onion, garlic, jalapeno peppers, cilantro and tomatoes in olive oil over a medium-low heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add chicken and stir in chicken stock.
Simmer gently until chicken is tender (approximately 20 minutes).
Remove chicken with a slotted spoon and set aside.
Add coconut milk to the pan and heat slowly until consistency is thick.
Add chicken; stir and heat throughout (about 10 minutes).
Serve with rice.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and margarine; stir in flour. Chill.
Divide dough into 24 balls.
Press into bottom of miniature muffin pans.
Combine egg, brown sugar and vanilla. Stir in nuts.
Fill cups 3/4 full of mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans.

title: marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well and place in a large Ziploc bag with the pork tenderloins.
Marinate for 3 hours. Drain marinade.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for approximately 45 to 60 minutes, basting as you cook.
Cool tenderloins.
Slice and return to marinade.
Heat and serve with party rye.

title: crabmeat stuffing muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add a few good dashes of season salt.
Spread onto muffins.
Cut muffins in half.
Put in fridge until hardened.
Place muffins into pieces.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Place under broiler for 2 to 5 minutes or until cheese is nice and browned.

title: barbecue dip for appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat to a boil.
Serve warm.

title: helen's molasses crinkles
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar; add eggs and stir well.
Mix in molasses and wheat germ.
Sift in white flour, salt, soda and spices stirring until well blended.
Add whole wheat flour stirring until well blended.

title: cheese cake beloved
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter, 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Line an 8-inch square pan, patting firmly.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Soften cream cheese to room temperature and beat smooth with 1/2 cup sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each.
Lastly add 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While cheese cake is cooling, combine sour cream, 1 1/4 cups sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour very, very gently over cooled cake.
Bake for 10 minutes more. Chill for 24 hours (not 1 minute less, for best results).

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water to 275° (hard crack stage).
Remove from heat.
Add peanuts, butter and vanilla.
Return to heat, stirring to 250°.
Add soda; remove from heat.
Stir to even consistency (frothy throughout).
Pour immediately on greased cookie sheet; do not spread, just pour.
Shake pan to evenly distribute.

title: lemon cool
directions: Mix nuts, oleo and flour together.
Pack into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: party potatoes
directions: Beat potatoes.
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
(If too stiff, add milk.)
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Season with garlic salt.
(I beat some butter in my potatoes and sprinkle the top with paprika.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: zucchini lemon muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda in a large bowl.
Combine zucchini, egg whites, applesauce, lemon juice, lemon peel and salt in a medium bowl; stir well.
Preheat oven. Spray muffin tin cups with nonstick cooking spray.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs well, gradually add sugar.
Add applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture, beating until smooth.
Add water, pumpkin and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased or sprayed pans at 325° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Can be frozen.

title: rice stuffed chicken
directions: Season inside of chicken with salt and pepper.
Melt margarine.
Add onions and saute until lightly browned.
Add rice; stir over medium heat until colored.
Add bouillon.
Stir and cover.
Cook until liquid is absorbed.
Add thyme and pepper to taste.
Let rice mixture cool and then stuff chicken.
Bake chicken at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste frequently with pan drippings.
Serves 5.

title: jeff's delight
directions: Mix together crushed pretzels (not too fine).
Add melted butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Put together in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: swabian maultaschen
directions: Mix flour, salt, eggs and water to make a smooth dough.
Let sit for 1 hour.
Wash spinach and steam until soft.
Chop onion and dice bacon.
Saute onion with the bacon.
Mix spinach, hamburger, onion and bacon.
Roll out dough very thin and cut in 4 to 5-inch squares.
Put mixture in middle of the square and put another square on top.
Spread egg white around edges of bottom square and press top square with fork to make a pocket.
Boil some beef broth and put maultaschen in.
Let simmer for about 10 minutes.
Guten appetit.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into 9-inch pie crust. Bake in preheated oven at 325° until firm. Good served warm or cold, with or without whipped topping. Makes 7 servings. Preparation time: 1:00.

title: smoked almonds
directions: Mix liquid smoke and water.
Add almonds and mix well.
Let stand overnight.
Drain almonds and place in a shallow pan.
Add oil and toss until well coated.
Roast in 300° oven for 25 minutes, stirring frequently.
When golden, sprinkle with salt.

title: sugar kisses(cookies)
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat eggs; add to mixture.
Add flour-salt mixture to batter.
Roll into teaspoon size balls.
Chill.
Cook at 400° for 10 minutes.
Place 1 Hershey's Kiss on top of each cookie while hot.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add flour and milk alternately, starting and ending with flour.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for an hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Cream butter and peanut butter until well blended.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat on low speed until light and fluffy.
Add one egg and beat on medium speed a full five minutes.
Add the remaining egg and beat another five minutes. Fold in whipped topping until well blended.
Pour into pie shell and freeze about 2 hours.

title: junior cook hamburgers(kids can fix for a party)
directions: Get out mother's heaviest skillet.
Put all ingredients in it. Cook over a medium flame for about 20 minutes, stirring frequently. Cut open the hamburger rolls and fill with mixture.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease 2 pans 9 x 5 x 3. Dust with flour.
Combine sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs, beat until fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice together.
Add pumpkin mixture alternately with water, mix well.
Divide into loaf pans, bake in 350 degree oven for 60 to 90 minutes or until center springs back.

title: diabetic banana cream pie
directions: Cut 2 bananas up in pudding mix; let set up.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins in 1 3/4 c. water for 5 minutes.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Moisten with remaining 1/4 c. cold water and add to raisins, stirring until mixture boils. Remove from fire and add butter or margarine and vinegar.
Pour mixture into a 9 inch pastry crust.
Cover top with pastry.
Bake at 425 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: mustard glazed pears
directions: Drain pears and place in shallow baking dish. Simmer together butter, sugar and mustard until well blended. Pour over pears and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pizza rice salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed and cool.
Lightly toss rice with remaining ingredients in a large bowl, using 1/2 cup of the dressing.
Chill.
Just before serving, toss remaining dressing into the salad.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
May not look done, but do not bake more at this time.

title: granola
directions: Mix and heat until hot the honey and safflower oil. Add the vanilla. Roast at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir twice while cooking and let cool in pan.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients. Add shrimp and eggs. Mix, chill and serve with Town House crackers.

title: mrs. ryder's cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° until done.

title: quiche
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: ham and cheese balls
directions: Form chopped ham and other ingredients into a ball.
Wrap up ball in 2 or 3 slices of ham.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Cream after each one.
Add flour and vanilla; mix with spoon by hand or with electric mixer.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
This cake is very good to eat under strawberries for shortcake.

title: quiche
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spray Pam in 2 small pie pans or 1 large pie pan.
Add mixture.
Place in oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water 8 to 10 minutes or until tender. Drain and set aside. In a large bowl, combine next 10 ingredients and 1 cup of the Swiss cheese; mix well, then fold in potatoes. Put in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly and lightly brown. Top with Cheddar and remaining Swiss cheeses. Sprinkle with paprika. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: zesty macaroni salad
directions: In a 1-quart bowl, combine macaroni, vegetables and parsley. In small bowl combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over macaroni mixture and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Toss again just before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: winter white pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Pour butter over pecans then bake for 15 minutes.
After removing from oven, sprinkle with salt.
In top of a double boiler, melt chocolate.
Using a toothpick, dip pecans in white chocolate.
Place on wax paper and cool.
Store in tin.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Mix and spread on assorted crackers or spread on toast rounds and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Serve at once.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 4 ingredients. Add the vinegar and beat for 4 minutes. Add the oil. Beat 10 minutes. Add poppy seed. Whisk in. Yields 2 3/4 cups. Good on most salads and fresh fruit.

title: easy peach cream pie
directions: Place peaches in pie shell.
Beat eggs slightly in bowl; blend in sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in cream and vanilla; blend well. Pour over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until center shakes slightly when moved.
To prevent crust edges from becoming too brown, cover edges with foil if desired.
Serve warm, or for firmer pie, chill before serving.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Boil chicken breast, then cut into strips.
In pan put oil and an onion.
Put chicken in and add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook until onions are done.
Take lid off and turn on high until water is cooked out.
Stuff meat into pita pockets.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except the bell peppers.
Wash the peppers well, cut off the tops and clean out the inside.
Rinse well.
In a 3-quart boiler, bring 2 quarts of water to a boil.
Drop the bell peppers into the water for 10 minutes.
Remove the peppers and place them on a 3-inch deep baking dish.
Spoon the meat mixture into the peppers.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream cake and cherries
directions: Cream together well the first 5 ingredients. Sift together, then add, the flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Get ready for middle of cake batter.
Mix the brown sugar and cinnamon together. Pour half of the batter in well-greased and floured pan, then add cherries, brown sugar, cinnamon and sugar in middle.
Add the other half of batter.
Top with cinnamon and sugar. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour 9x9x2-inch loaf pan.
Soak raisins in sherry.
Toast bread, spread with butter and cut into triangles.
Layer bread buttered side up in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and raisins.
In a separate bowl, pour milk and sugar into eggs, beating rapidly.
Stir in remaining sherry and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Bake about 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted into center. Serve warm or cold with cream or half-and half.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add soda, blend shortening with salt, spices and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, vanilla and cooled raisins.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water until tender; drain. Combine noodles, drained tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt. Blend soup and milk; heat thoroughly.
Add cheese; heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with almonds.
Bake in hot oven (425°) about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
You may skip some of the ingredients if you wish.
I add some green peas.

title: rice-a-roni chicken salad
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Add chopped bell pepper, scallions, black olives and cooked Rice-A-Roni.
Cool and refrigerate.
Add reserved artichoke oil and mayonnaise 30 minutes before serving.

title: sea island tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Stir in mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Blend with sour cream and seasonings.
Gently stir in sweet peas and remaining ingredients.

title: carrots and rutabaga
directions: Cook rutabaga and carrots in a small amount of boiling salted water until tender.
Drain.
Mash a little.
Add butter and seasonings.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: Put ham, sausages, onions and green pepper in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium heat until vegetables are soft (meat will provide enough fat for cooking).
Add rice, paprika, salt, parsley and thyme.
Stir and cook for 5 minutes. Add the boiling water.
Increase heat, bring to a boil and let boil for 5 minutes.
Stir; then cover tightly.
Reduce heat and cook until rice is tender, about 35 minutes.
Serves about 5.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend buttermilk, sugar and melted oleo.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in vanilla and cinnamon.
Blend thoroughly and pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients; add remaining ingredients. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour into pan and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Frost, if desired.

title: glazed oranges with kiwi
