directions: Cut thin slivers of peel from one orange with a vegetable parer or sharp knife, being careful not to cut into white membrane.
Cover peel with boiling water; let stand 5 minutes. Drain.

title: frosted orange
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Fill remainder of blender with ice cubes.
Blend until ice is crushed and drink is frothy. Enjoy!

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add all remaining ingredients except nuts and marshmallows.
Mix.
Dough will be very stiff and dry.
Chill dough, then roll into 1-inch balls and place each ball on top of a cluster of finely chopped nuts on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove.
Place 1/2 of large marshmallow, cut side down on each cookie and return to oven for 2 minutes.
Cool cookies, then frost.

title: barbados beef and rice
directions: Brown beef with scallions in a large skillet, breaking beef into small pieces.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, olives and chili powder.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir with a fork.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook, bone and cut chicken into small pieces.
Chop onion and cook with green chilies in 1/2 stick oleo until onion is clear. Add soup and milk and cook until bubbly.
Butter all sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan and layer the bottom with corn chips.
Add the chicken pieces.
Layer with half of grated cheese and pour soup mixture over all.
Spread another layer of corn chips and remainder of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves better if allowed to set 15 minutes before serving.
Can be prepared ahead and frozen.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Spoon sauce over hot cake.

title: bernice's surprise(cake)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with spoon.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken until tender; bone and skin.
Set aside.
Grate onion.
Add cornbread, toasted bread, margarine, poultry seasoning and cream of chicken soup.
Pour chicken broth over this and add all of chicken but breast.
Mix well and add eggs.
Mix again.
Put dressing in buttered pan.
Divide chicken breast and place on top of dressing.
Bake slow at about 300° until brown and done in center.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: old time scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange layer of potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with some of the onions.
Sprinkle with some salt, pepper and flour.
Dot with some of butter. Repeat layers until all are used up, ending with butter.
Pour milk over all and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake covered for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes more or until tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased casserole dish.
Save some cheese to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs (optional).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until bubbly or microwave 15 minutes on High.

title: chicken in wine or sherry
directions: Combine sugar with Bisquick. Wet chicken, then dip into Bisquick mix. Brown in hot grease; add salt and pepper, onion, garlic, wine or sherry and a little water, salt again. Cover and steam until well done.

title: cornish hen bake
directions: Pout 2 1/2 cups boiling water over dry salad dressing mix.
Add chicken soup.
Lay hens over top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: grandma's banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, salt, 1/2 cup sugar, egg yolks and milk.
Cook on very low fire or in top of double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla extract.
(Microwave works very well. Cook until boiling, stirring often.)

title: one of everything pancakes
directions: In a bowl combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar and salt. In another bowl beat egg, milk and oil. Stir into dry ingredients, justs until moistened. Drop by 1/4 c. onto a lightly greased hot pan. Turn when bubbles form on top of pancakes, turn and cook on other side till brown.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Thaw hash brown potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mix in the thawed potatoes and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with the cornflakes mixed with oleo.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 8 to 10.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk to a boil 1 minute. Add remaining ingredients.
Nuts may be added for variety.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Makes about 40 cookies that taste like fudge when cool.

title: chocolate chip sugar cookies
directions: Beat oleo, sugar, egg, sour cream and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips and dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, minced onion, egg, milk, bread crumbs, salt and pepper and shape into meatballs and brown in skillet. Remove excess fat.
Combine the following ingredients:
tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and seasoned salt.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer over low heat 10 to 15 minutes, turning frequently to glaze all meatballs.

title: honeyed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown chops in small amount of oil. Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
(Do not salt.)
Combine remaining ingredients except sesame seed.
Pour over chops. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Lightly brown sausage; add water.
Combine other ingredients and add to sausage.
Mix.
Put into a butter greased casserole. Dot with 2 tablespoons butter and bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper.
Stir in vegies and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until mixture begins to bubble.
Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into quarters.
Remove dish from oven; stir.
Arrange biscuit pieces over hot chicken mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until biscuits are golden brown.
Makes 5 servings.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Combine first six ingredients in a bowl.
Stir thoroughly to blend. cover and refrigerate at least one hour.

title: chewy granola bars
directions: Melt together marshmallows and butter.
Add oil, honey, and peanut butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Spread in 11 x 15 in. pan.
Cut in bars.
For best storage, keep in refrigerator.

title: locke-ober's french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil; mix well, then add oil.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in roaster.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Drain.
Make sauce with remaining ingredients and brush on ribs. Return to oven; reduce heat to 300° and bake for another hour or until tender.
Baste several times while cooking.

title: flounder paisano
directions: Sprinkle flounder with garlic salt and pepper.
Place in baking dish.
Add oregano and wine vinegar to tomato juice.
Pour over fish.
Broil about 3-inches from heat for 10 minutes or until fish flakes.
Serves 2.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder; set aside. Mix shortening and peanut butter.
Add both kinds of sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour mixture.
Drop dough from teaspoon onto cookie sheet, flattening dough with a fork. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Yields 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: krispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugar at medium speed until creamed; add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Combine flour and other ingredients (if you are not using self-rising flour) to shortening mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and cereal by hand (not mixer). Shape into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: mama nellie's cherry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add milk; blend thoroughly.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crush Doritos chips in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add hamburger, beans and taco sauce.
Layer with lettuce, tomato bits, pepper and cheese.
Heat at 350° until cheese melts, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Break eggs into a large bowl; beat until foamy. Beat in honey, molasses combination or brown sugar; add vanilla and salt.
Stir in grated coconut, nuts or wheat germ.
Add whole wheat flour and stir until mixed well.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine chicken, fruit and celery; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, combine chicken mixture, dressing and nuts.
Serve in hollowed out pineapple shell.

title: diet banana split pie
directions: Mix graham crackers and margarine and press into pie pan. Slice banana over crust.
Sprinkle pineapple over banana.
Mix pudding with milk and pour over fruit.
Top with Cool Whip. Serves 4.
Each serving counts as 1 bread, 1 milk, 1 fruit, 1 fat; 50 optional calories if Cool Whip is used.

title: cheddar baked chicken
directions: Note:
For more attractive servings, use only thighs and breast.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth.
Grease heated griddle.
To test griddle, sprinkle with few drops of water.
If water skittles around, heat is right.
Pour batter onto hot griddle.
Turn pancakes as soon as they are puffed and full of bubbles, but before bubbles break.
Bake other side until golden brown.

title: grilled honey-bourbon salmon
directions: Thaw salmon if frozen.
Rinse fish, pat dry, place in plastic bag set in a shallow baking dish.
In a small bowl, stir together bourbon, brown sugar, honey, soy sauce, ginger and pepper.
Pour over fish in bag.
Close bag.
Marinate fish in refrigerator one hour, turning occasionally.
Drain fish, reserving marinade.
Coat rack with oil or spray.
Place fish on rack of uncovered grill directly over medium heat.
Grill 8 to 12 minutes or until fish begins to flake easily with fork, turning once.
Brush once with reserved marinade half-way through grilling time.
Discard remaining marinade.
Serves:

title: chip dip
directions: Shred lettuce and chop tomatoes; make layers.
Top layer is shredded cheese.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Spread in a 9 inch baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-30 minutes. Serve with crackers. Rye bagel chip crackers are great with this.

title: billy t's clam chowder
directions: Peel and boil potatoes in stock until almost tender.
Have 1 3/4 quarts half and half warm as your clams.
Add warm half and half to potatoes and stock.
Do not let boil.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and cover casserole.
Bake in a 400° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: ham and potato skillet
directions: Slice potatoes and cook, covered, about 15 minutes or until tender.
(Add beans last 5 minutes.)
Drain.

title: microwave fudge pie
directions: Put butter and chocolate in a glass mixing bowl.
Place in microwave
oven and cook on High 30 to 45 seconds or until melted. Add sugar to melted butter and chocolate.	Beat well. Add	eggs; beat well.	Stir in flour and vanilla.
Beat well. Add
pecans. Pour into a 9-inch ungreased pie plate.
Cook in microwave on High 6 minutes, rotating often.	Top with vanilla ice cream if desired.

title: blueberry icebox pie
directions: Mix and pour into pan and cook 30 minutes at 250°.
Cool and pour in can blueberry pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix and pour over the first layer.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend sugar and cornstarch; mix with water and cook until thickened.
Mix in strawberry Jell-O and let cool.
Slice strawberries and place in prebaked pastry shell.
Then pour cooled mixture over the strawberries.
Chill well before serving.

title: cottage cheese souffle salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water, vinegar, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and cottage cheese.
Beat well together and let thicken in refrigerator enough to beat light and fluffy, then add celery, onion, pimiento, eggs and lettuce.
Mix well all together.
Pour in dish and keep in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix 2 cups of boiling water with package of Jell-O. Add pineapple, pie filling and nuts. Chill in the refrigerator. Top with a mixture of cream cheese, sour cream and sugar. Chill.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat after adding each one.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Add alternately with milk and sour cream to egg mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour 30 minutes.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour in prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set.
Top with sour cream.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool. Chill.
Top with fruit.

title: ham ball
directions: Leave cream cheese out to soften.
Chop all of the ham real fine.
Reserve enough to roll ham ball in, and set aside.
Now take the soften cream cheese, and put in a bowl, and grate onion on top.
Then add the chopped pimento.
Mix ham with cheese mixture.
Pour worcestershire sauce in, and
mix real good with your hands.
Roll into ball with wet hands.
Then place the ball on plate with reserved ham, and
cover the ball real good on top and sides with reserved ham.
Place on tray and cover with plastic wrap, until ready to serve.
You can make early.
Serve with veg. crackers or wheat or even Ritz crackers.

title: grandma leonard's coconut pie
directions: Cook on top of stove until it thickens.
Use medium heat and stir while cooking.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: party rice
directions: Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for about an hour.
Stir occasionally.
This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: herbal bread
directions: Thaw bread dough overnight in refrigerator.
Allow to rise at room temperature for 1 hour.
Melt margarine and add remaining ingredients; set aside.
Knead both loaves of bread into 1 ball. Roll ball into a 12-inch square, cut into 25 squares.
Dip each square of dough into herb mixture and place in greased Bundt pan, overlapping each square slightly.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until fully baked.
Best served warm.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In pot, cook pineapple syrup, sugar and butter until sugar is dissolved.
Pour syrup in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange pineapple slices with cherries in center.
Pour cake mixture over syrup and pineapple slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes, then turn onto platter.

title: linda white's italian beef(spicy hot)
directions: Roast beef until rare.
Cut into slices or chunks.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer all day.
Serve on sliced French bread.

title: quick pickled peaches
directions: Drain syrup from peaches.
Add brown sugar, vinegar and spices.
Boil mixture 5 minutes.
Add peach halves and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Yields
7 to 8 servings.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Break crackers coarsely into pastry lined pan.
Boil water, sugar and cream of tartar for 15 minutes (gently).
Add lemon juice and rind; cool.
Pour syrup over crackers; dot generously with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put on pastry top and slit top.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: heavenly fruit salad(yields 12 to 16 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: cheese carrots
directions: Scrape 2 packages carrots.
Slice 1/2-inch thick and cook until tender in salted water.
Melt butter and cheese.
Pour over carrots.
Bake in a casserole dish 30 minutes at 350°, about 10 minutes before taking out of oven.
Cover with bread crumbs and let brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients, adding cut strawberries or other fruit last.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini saute
directions: Cut washed and trimmed zucchini into 1/2-inch slices.
Saute onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Reduce heat, add zucchini and cook until tender-crisp, stirring often.
Stir in salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix well.

title: licking good salad
directions: Mix together the jello and water in a 9-inch square pan.
Let set until partially thickened.
Mix in prepared Dream Whip, cream cheese, maraschino cherries, drained pineapple and nuts. Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given and mix well.
Drop from tablespoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon orange roughy bake
directions: In a pie plate, combine butter and lemon juice; set aside. In another pie plate, combine bread crumbs, lemon pepper, seasoned salt and dill weed.
Wash fillets; pat dry with paper towels.
Dip each fillet in butter mixture, then in bread crumb mixture.
Place in an ungreased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining butter mixture over fillets; sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish begins to flake when tested with a fork.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Open rolls and place 4 rectangles on ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until browned. Cool.
Beat cream cheese, sour cream and seasonings until smooth. Spread evenly over cooled crust; cover.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Before serving, top with vegetables cut into squares.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Stir in marshmallows.
Fold in whip cream.
Cover and let set in fridge overnight.

title: dirt pudding
directions: First Layer:
Place cookie crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch serving dish.
Pour melted margarine over crumbs. Refrigerate.

title: orange salad delight
directions: Mix jello (dry) with cottage cheese. Drain juice off pineapple and oranges.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 1 hour and it's ready to eat.

title: egg noodles
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Add flour until dough is stiff enough to roll out on floured sheet.
Roll out thin (1/8-inch or less); cut into strips (1/4 to 3/8-inch wide).
Let dry one hour.
Drop into boiling broth and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: stroganoff
directions: Combine soups with browned meat.
Simmer 15 to 30 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Mix crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt, paprika and pepper.
Dip chops in egg, then in crumbs.
Brown in oil.
Place slice of Mozzarella cheese in each.
Mix tomato sauce, garlic, wine, oregano and Sweet 'N Low.
Pour over chops.
Simmer 50 minutes.
Serve with linguini.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked carmel apples
directions: Bake apples at 350° until crispy on outside.
Test with knife, inside will be soft.
Melt carmels in saucepan.
Remove apples from oven.
Place on plate.
Pour melted carmels over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Let cool eat right away or refrigerate for later.
Add popsicle stick for easy eating!

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine other ingredients and pour over melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Combine browned meat, tomato sauce and seasoning mix; simmer 5 minutes.
Press crescent rolls on bottom and sides of pizza pan, pressing edges together to form seal.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until brown.
Fill with meat mixture; cover with Velveeta cubes.
Bake until cheese melts.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with sour cream if desired.

title: strata
directions: Grease a glass baking dish (8 1/2 x 11-inch).
Mix together the eggs and milk.
Layer white or wheat bread on bottom of baking dish (cut off crusts).
Layer vegetables (onion, green pepper and mushrooms), then cheese, then meat.
Pour mixture of eggs and milk over layer.
Top with extra cheese. Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take out; let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients adding liquid slowly.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix in glass casserole dish and bake at 350° until brown.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a deep saucepan, heat butter and oil to medium.
Add onions and celery and stir.
Cook 5 minutes.
Dust on flour and mix well. Add broth, 2 cans of water and broccoli.
Stir and bring to boil. Reduce heat to low, cover and cook 15 minutes.

title: goodie nut bars
directions: Combine chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter in microwave dish.
Microwave on High for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, or until softened, stirring once.
Stir until smooth.
Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with waxed paper.
Spoon 1/2 of chocolate mixture into pan; spread evenly.
Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour, or freeze 15 minutes.

title: easy as pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baked pie shells. If limeade is used, put in green food coloring.

title: one-hour rolls
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm.
Add shortening. Mix yeast and sugar in a cup and pour in a little warm milk to dissolve.
Add to the other liquid mixture and add dry ingredients.
Knead, using more flour if necessary.
Roll out dough as if for biscuits, cut and put in pans.
Let rise for 45 minutes and bake at 400°.

title: easy no-bake cheesecake
directions: Whip cream cheese and add sugar slowly.
Blend in Cool Whip. Spread evenly in pie shell.
Top with pie filling and refrigerate.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Pour pineapple with juice into a buttered 11 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine flour and sugar.
Sprinkle over pineapple. Cover with layer of cracker crumbs and cheese.
Pour melted oleo over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Before baking, brush or pour on chicken, pork spareribs or beef ribs.
"One recipe will be enough for 2 pounds of meat.
Delicious!"

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: hawaiian carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut in 1/2-inch diagonal slices.
Cook carrots
in
small	amount	of
water until almost done.
Heat juice
and	water,	reserving
1/4 cup.
Mix salt, cornstarch, sugar
and	lemon
juice in the 1/4 cup reserved liquid.
Cook until
thick
and clear.
Add pineapple and pour over carrots. Let simmer until ready to serve.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in glass dish; I use a quiche dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.
Serve hot with Triscuits.

title: creole red beans
directions: Soak red beans in about 6 cups of cold water overnight.
In a large pot, saute ham in salad oil until lightly browned.
Add chopped onions.
Saute until transparent, but not brown, stirring constantly.
Add red beans and more water to cover.
Cook over low heat 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally to prevent from sticking, also add more water if necessary.
When beans are done, mix flour with tomato sauce, stirring to make a smooth paste and stir into beans.
Add red pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes more.
Serve over cooked rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: curry chicken divan(from the litton microwave book)
directions: Place frozen chopped broccoli in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole. Cover with glass lid; microwave 8 minutes on High, or until partly cooked and set aside.
Arrange turkey slices in a single layer over bottom of 10-inch glass ceramic skillet.
Combine remaining ingredients, except broccoli, in medium mixing bowl; mix well. Pour over turkey slices; top with cooked broccoli.
Cover tightly with glass lid.
Microwave for 15 to 17 minutes on High or until rice is tender (about 150°).
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Blend cake mix, 1 package of the pudding mix, eggs, soda and oil.
Cook in Bundt or tube pan for 50 minutes at 350°.
When cake is completely cooled, frost with other package of prepared pudding mix.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Stir in one to two spoonfuls of tea with hot water.

title: hoke's banana-caramel pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in a saucepan.
Stir in cold water, egg yolks and milk.
Gradually stir in boiling water.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Remove from stove and add butter and vanilla. Cool.
Spread in a baked pie shell and push bananas (slices) down into filling.
Whip the cream and cover pie shortly before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: hard pretzel snack
directions: Pour mixture of oil, dressing, seasoning and dill weed over pretzel pieces; stir.
Place pretzels on flat cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir once during baking time.

title: split pea soup
directions: Into a 4-quart container, with a heavy bottom, put split peas, beef bone and cold water.
Place container over medium heat and bring to boiling point.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all together in
a large bowl and mix.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4s and mix with the melted butter. Mix together the remaining ingredients. Mix with the dough pieces. Put into tube pan and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheese cookie
directions: Roll out 1 cookie dough between wax paper.
Put in bottom of ungreased 9x13 pan.
Meanwhile, mix together cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Spread this over layer of cookie dough.
Roll out other cookie dough and pat on top of cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts over top if you wish.
Bake 350° for 45 mins.

title: cajun stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in margarine until clear.
Add shrimp; cover and cook until shrimp are pink.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, mushrooms and soup.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sour cream just before serving.
Serve over rice or pasta.
Garnish with chives. Serves 4 to 6.

title: italian sausage pie
directions: Saute sausage and onions; drain and add to pie pan.
Blend eggs, cream (milk), cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour over filling. Bake until custard forms in 350° oven for about 35 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Cut in 6 to 8 slices.

title: party taco dip
directions: Mix in bowl sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning; set aside.
Cut around avocado pit; scoop out and mash (don't use skin).
Cut up in small pieces ripe tomatoes and olives.
Cut scallions in small pieces.
In long dish, layer ingredients: avocado, sour cream, mayo, taco seasoning mix, tomatoes, olives, scallions and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with nacho chips and get ready to give out the recipe!

title: sue ellen's chili
directions: Mix ground round and pork.
Brown.
Add onion and celery; continue browning, until onion begins to look clear.
Drain excess fat.
Add all ingredients.
Cover and simmer one hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put broccoli, bacon, sunflower nuts, raisins and red onion slices in salad bowl.
Combine Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar. Pour over salad and toss.

title: frozen pink fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot fruit juice.
Add marshmallows while still hot.
Dissolve.
Cool in refrigerator until it begins to congeal.
Whip until smooth.
Add fruit and Dream Whip.
Freeze.

title: petite cherry cheesecake
directions: Using muffin pans, put vanilla wafers in paper baking cups. Fill cups 2/3 full with cream cheese mixture (first 5 ingredients blended with mixer until smooth).
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with pie filling and chill.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly oil or spray with nonstick spray a large baking sheet.
Place kidney beans and oil in a medium bowl and mash with a fork or a potato masher.
Sprinkle evenly with cumin, chili powder and garlic powder.
Mix well. Add green chilies, mix again.

title: mom's angel food dessert
directions: Mix lemon jello, pineapple juice and hot water and let congeal.
Then whip.
Add pineapple and beaten eggs.
Arrange a layer of cake and layer of pineapple mixture in a large 9 x 13-inch pan which has been oiled.
(Can be put in larger pan.) Serves 12.

title: cracker salad
directions: Dice tomato, onion and cucumber in a large bowl.
Crumble crackers in bowl; add mayo or salad dressing.
Mix and serve.

title: salmon bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole that has been sprayed with vegetable oil.
Bake for 35 minutes or until bubbling.

title: raisin apple cinnamon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add to oil mixture; blend well.
Stir in apples, walnuts and raisins.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake in hot oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
Serve with vanilla ice cream if desired.
Makes 16 servings.

title: beef-broccoli wellington
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, brown meat; drain well. Add broccoli, cheese, onion, sour cream, salt and pepper; mix well.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: steak salad italiano
directions: Preheat broiler.
Put steak on broiler pan.
Broil 6 inches from heat, 3 to 5 minutes on each side, depending on desired doneness.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Slice steak into thin strips. Put steak, green pepper, basil, onion, dressing, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Toss to mix.
Add cheese; gently toss.
Cover; chill.
Separate lettuce.
Arrange on serving platter.
Spoon salad over lettuce.
Garnish with tomatoes.
Makes 4 servings. Prep. Time:
10 minutes.
Cooking Time:
10 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground meat and diced onions in big frypan that has a cover. (Make sure the pan will hold all the ingredients, including the soup and extra water.) Drain off extra fat, etc. from ground meat. Pour in optionals (including liquid from cans). Pour in tomato soup. Add 1 can of water if no optionals were used. Pour in lots of chili powder. Add a dash of dry red pepper if you choose. Cover pot. Put on low heat. Taste after 15 minutes to see if you have enough chili powder. If not, add more. If too hot, add a little water if you must. This is ready in 1/2 hour, but is better if you let it simmer.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and slice in casserole dish.
Pat hamburger over potatoes.
Pour vegetable soup and mushroom soup over top of hamburger.
Sprinkle crushed chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Heat to rolling boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 1 minute without stirring.
Place saucepan in bowl of ice water.
Beat until frosting is smooth and spreading consistency.
Stir in vanilla.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add flour until thick.
Hand roll balls and place 2-inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350° about 7 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pour into pie crusts. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Toss all ingredients. Spoon onto salad greens.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour with sugar, dry milk, baking powder and salt.
Stir in cereal and raisins.
Mix eggs, bananas, butter and water; add to flour.
Stir just until all flour is moist.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack. Wrap in plastic or aluminum and store overnight before slicing. Makes 1 loaf.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Brown under broiler.

title: beef roast
directions: Brown
roast
on all sides.
Place roast on large sheet of heavy-duty	foil
in
baking
pan.	Sprinkle soup mix over roast. Spread canned mushroom soup all over roast.
Seal foil securely over roast.
Bake at 400° for 4 hours.

title: easy sweet potato or yam pie
directions: In food processor bowl, combine all ingredients except pie shell. Process until well-blended. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean and pie is golden-brown.

title: christmas ornaments
directions: Combine cinnamon and applesauce in a plastic bag.
Mix well. Put out on piece of waxed paper.
Roll out to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Transfer to cookie sheet.
Poke hole in appropriate place for ribbon.
Air dry 2 to 3 days.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
For 1 cup of tea, use 2 heaping teaspoons, then share a quite moment with a friend.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine chopped vegetables, salt and sugar; simmer until mixture starts to thicken.
Then add vinegar and spices and cook down until it becomes a thick sauce.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Boil in jars for 15 minutes.
This makes 3 quarts.

title: buffalo potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, blend ingredients and add potatoes, turning to coat.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 45 minutes or until potatoes are crisp.
Serve with dressing.

title: "shake it" pie crust
directions: In bowl with lid, add flour, salt and shortening.
Shake it. Add ice water.
Shake it until it thuds.
Makes 2 (8-inch) pie crusts.

title: pop up rolls
directions: Mix well.
Melt pat of butter in each muffin tin.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: cajun chili
directions: Put flour and grease in pot and cook until dark brown; add salt and pepper to taste.
When roux is almost dark, add onion and garlic.
Always keep stirring to keep roux from sticking.
Now, add your chili meat or whatever kind of meat you choose (deer meat is good).
When meat is browned, start adding your beans, sauce and tomatoes.
Add chili powder to taste and cook on low fire until desired.
Now eat.

title: cucumber (or zucchini) relish
directions: Grind vegetables, put in pan, add 1/4 cup salt and 3 quarts water.
Let set 2 1/2 hours.
Drain water.
Add celery salt, ground mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: broc-a-roli
directions: Saute onion and butter.
Steam rice.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Grate cheese and save a small amount to sprinkle on top.

title: eggnog
directions: Combine a little of each: grape juice, vinegar, mustard, mayonnaise, juice from 1 lemon, pepper, salt, ketchup, olive oil and a little piece of onion.
Drink and in no time freckles will appear!

title: chicken (or turkey) casserole
directions: Mix melted butter into seasoning mix.
Put all but 3/4 cup of the mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat it down.
Save the rest for topping.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and form into balls the size of quarters. Brown on all sides.
Pour off grease.
Place onion rings over meat balls.
Combine last ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over meat balls and onions.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour over browned pieces of chicken in saucepan; simmer 1 hour.
Great for leftover fried chicken.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute onion
in
butter
with garlic powder and pepper. Add shrimp and stir-fry over medium heat about 5 to 10 minutes or until done.
Remove shrimp with slotted spoon. Add wine and lemon juice
(previously mixed) to remaining butter.
Simmer 2 minutes. Serve on a bed of rice.

title: puttanesca
directions: In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat.
Add bacon, garlic, onions, and chilis, saute only until bacon begins to brown, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, breaking them up with your hands.
Stir in spices.
Boil until thick, 15 to 20 minutes. Stir in parmesan cheese just before serving.
Serve over spaghetti, linguine, fettuccini, fusilli, or pasta shells.
Serves 6.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Serves 75 to 80 people.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle top with powdered sugar

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all the above together and put in a greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Mix ingredients altogether.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cow pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, taco seasoning and onion.
Spread on tray.
Top with tomato, cheese and green pepper. Serve with nacho chips.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok or large skillet.
Scramble beaten eggs.
Remove and set aside.
Heat the other 2 tablespoons oil to 400°.
Stir-fry rice, breaking up lumps, turning quickly and constantly.
When well heated, add salt, soy sauce, pork, onions and eggs.
Stir-fry to heat thoroughly.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy. Add oil, zucchini, sugar and vanilla. Mix lightly. Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder. Add nuts. Put in 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour, or until done (golden brown).

title: pizza beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
In a baking dish, layer in first beans, then meat mixture, followed by the spaghetti sauce.
On top of the sauce, put the pepperoni, then the Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: special delivery chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine the sour cream, soup and celery seeds. Stir in chicken.
Pour into a greased (11 x 7 x 2-inch) baking dish.
Combine the cracker crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: mexi-mac casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In saucepan, heat the no bean chili, tomato juice, green chilies and green onions.
Combine macaroni and chili mixture and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Crush 1 cup tortilla chips and spread on bottom of 3-quart baking dish.
Spoon in macaroni mixture.
Top with remaining chips and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish top with sour cream, tomatoes and cilantro.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake as directed on package.
While cake is warm, poke holes all over with fork.
Mix Jell-O with 1 cup hot water; stir in strawberry soda.
Pour over cake.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed on package; fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cake.
Refrigerate.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Fill each cheesecake. Put dab of jelly (strawberry, raspberry, apricot, etc.) in middle and bake for 5 more minutes. WILL FREEZE GREAT!

title: liverwurst dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Serve with crackers.

title: crusty garlic bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In sm. bowl, combine garlic and oil, mix well.
In another small bowl, combine parsley, thyme, marjoram and paprika.
Add Parmesan, mix well.
Cut each loaf crosswise into diagonal slices, without cutting all the way through.
Brush cut sides of slices with garlic oil.
Sprinkle herd mixture between slices.
Wrap each loaf in foil and bake about 10 to 15 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: In large frying pan melt butter or margarine.
Add chopped garlic and cook until soft.
Stir in flour and cook over low heat 1 minute.
Gradually add clam liquid, half and half, wine, thyme and pepper flakes.	Bring to a boil and simmer for 2 minutes. Stir in clams, parsley, lemon juice and Parmesan cheese.
Heat thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.	Cook linguini.	Drain well.
Pour sauce over pasta and mix gently.

title: chocolate chip glaze
directions: Heat over low heat until chocolate melts and blended.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot; cook on low 4 to 8 hours.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Place cooked noodles in large casserole dish.
Reames noodles are the best (frozen food department).
Mix soup, milk (broth) and salt.
Heat, stirring in cheese until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over noodles.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry crunch cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pie filling in bottom of pan. Spread cake mix over cherries.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Pour butter over all.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: kid-kolored pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl to blend.
Fry as pancakes, as directed on biscuit package.
Makes 16 servings.

title: souppa lahaniki greek winter vegetable(high protein)
directions: Soak beans overnight, then cook in fresh water.
Put cabbage, celery, carrots and tomatoes in large pot with 2 quarts of water, then cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to moderate and cook 20 minutes.
Add beans, potatoes, macaroni, garlic and savory. Season with salt and pepper and cook 20 minutes longer, until macaroni and potatoes are soft.
Heat oil in small pan and brown cubed bread until crisp, then add bread and oil to soup.
Stir well; remove from heat and let stand, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
If thicker than desired, add water and reheat. Serve with grated hard cheese or Parmesan.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening. Add sugar and cream, then add the eggs one at a time
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Add vanilla. Bake in a greased and flour 9 or 10 inch tube pan at 325 degrees for about 80 minutes or until done.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until smooth.
Add flour, milk, vanilla, coconut, then butter.
Grease 2 glass pie plates.
Bake at 250° or 300° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake #1
directions: Layer ingredients in order in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: ann's pasta
directions: Cook pasta 10 minutes in boiling, salted water; drain.
Toss with butter and garlic powder.
Pour in stewed Italian tomatoes and pasta sauce.
Place in Pyrex dish and cover with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with sourdough bread, piping hot. Serves 6 people.

title: easy day pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously after each addition.
Blend in vanilla, then flour gradually.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake one hour or until test of cake shows it is done.

title: corn casserole
directions: In microwave, heat cream cheese and butter until warm. Add corn and chilies. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars with 1/2 cup butter.
Cream remaining butter with sugar, then add eggs.
Add flour and baking soda alternately with milk.
Add melted bars, vanilla and nuts.
Pour this into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook the salt pork slowly in a large, heavy skillet.
Add the onion, green pepper, potato and butter or margarine and saute slowly for 15 to 20 minutes or until potato is tender.
Add salt, black pepper and corn and heat, stirring, until corn has thawed. Stir in parsley and milk; simmer gently, stirring, until corn is done.
Do not boil.
Serve at once.

title: apple cake
directions: Put apples in bowl; break eggs over apples.
Add other ingredients; mix together.
Bake in a greased, slightly floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add flour.
Stir until creamy.
Add corn and whipping cream.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Put water and butter in large pot and boil. Break up meat and cook 30 minutes. Add other ingredients. Simmer several hours. Add salt and hot sauce to taste.

title: italian chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together rice, onions, tomatoes, cheese, and 1 tsp. Italian seasoning.
Place in a greased 9-inch x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken and remaining seasoning. Bake 40 to 45 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: white and dark chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat butter, margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Beat in flour mixture until just combined.
Stir in chocolates.
Drop by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake until edges are brown but centers are still slightly soft (10 minutes).
Cool on baking sheets for 5 minutes before cooling on a rack.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: gloria belle's lasagna
directions: Combine Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, cottage cheese and eggs. Spread a layer of uncooked noodles, then a layer of cheese mixture into 9 x 13 pan. Mix pasta sauce with dry sauce mix. Spread a layer of sauce over cheese. Add a layer of hamburger and then sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers, ending with Mozzarella cheese. Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and beat until creamy and well mixed.
Place in three 9-inch cake pans, well-greased and floured. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into molds or 9 x 13-inch pan. Best if made night before.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all ingredients except coconut and mix well. Stir in coconut and pour into baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm to the touch and nicely browned.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and baking powder. Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Add the zucchini.
Mix well.
Add the nuts and raisins (optional).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: melty cheese
directions: Blend all ingredients until very smooth, then add 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Heat in heavy saucepan until thickened, stirring continuously.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain.
Melt cheese in microwave.
Mix all ingredients together.
Keep hot in crock-pot.
Serve with nachos.

title: scalloped potatoes, tomatoes and ham
directions: Lightly grease slow cooker.
Layer half of each ingredient in the order listed.
Repeat layers.
Cover and cook on high setting for 1 hour.
Reduce to low setting. Cook 5 to 6 hours or until potatoes are tender. Stir before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar and stir until it is dissolved.
Add the other ingredients.
Refrigerate until partly set.
Stir and return to refrigerator until set.
Serve on lettuce.

title: pretzel snacks
directions: Mix and pour over pretzels.
Stir well until pretzels are all coated.
Spread on a cookie sheet and bake for 5 minutes at 250°, stirring at least one time.
Store in a salad container such as a plastic jar or Baggies.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Roll cut biscuit pieces into a ball and toss in cinnamon sugar.
Place coated biscuits into tube pan.
Melt margarine and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie(from kitchen's restaurant)
directions: Combine cheese and peanut butter.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add topping and powdered sugar.
Spoon into cooked crusts and freeze 8 hours or overnight.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple date streusel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 8-inch round cake pan.
Melt brown sugar and butter or margarine together; add flour and chopped nuts; mix well until crumbly.
Set aside.
In bowl, stir muffin mix, dates and milk until moistened.
Evenly pour half of batter into prepared pan and top with half of streusel mixture. Spread remaining batter over top and sprinkle with remaining streusel.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serve warm.

title: nut cake
directions: Bring to boil margarine, water and cocoa.
In separate bowl mix together well, flour, sugar and salt.
Pour margarine and cocoa mixture into flour and sugar mixture, blending well,
In separate bowl, beat eggs, sour cream and soda.
Add egg and sour cream mixture to chocolate and flour mixture.
Pour into a greased cookie sheet
(18 x 18 inches) 1 inch deep.
Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
While cake is baking make
icing.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix as directed on package.
Add butter and beat together cream cheese and eggs.
Add powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar. Add other ingredients and mix well. Put in a greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Leave in pan for a little while, but loosen cake from sides. Top with following glaze.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: ham fried rice
directions: Pour cooking oil in skillet, add cut-up onions and tops to oil and cook for 2 minutes (over low heat).
Add cut-up ham, cook for a minute or 2. Add frozen peas and the cold cooked rice.
Mix well and heat until rice is hot.

title: tortilla appetizer
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients for filling. Spread filling over tortillas and roll up. Slice about thickness of your finger and arrange on serving plate. Serve salsa, green onions and olives; let people put on as much as desired.

title: english muffins in a loaf
directions: Measure
cups
flour by spooning lightly into a cup. Combine
flour,
yeast,
sugar, salt and baking soda.
Combine milk
and
water and heat to 120° to 130°.
Add to dry mixture and beat well.
Stir in enough more flour to make a very stiff batter. Spoon
batter into 2 greased loaf pans that have been sprinkled with
cornmeal.
Sprinkle tops with cornmeal, cover, and let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.

title: miriam's jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Melt cream cheese and oleo in double boiler.
Mix flour, salt and milk and add to cream cheese.
Add the corn and peppers to the mixture.
Pour in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish or roasting pan.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top of chicken.
Seal with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 35 minutes. Take off foil and let brown for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve.

title: pancho's hot dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender, mixing well, then heat to boil (do not cool).

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake together biscuits and 4 tablespoons cinnamon.
Grease tube pan (option, put nuts in bottom).
Drop mixture in pan.
Take 1 1/2 sticks of butter (not margarine), 2 large tablespoons cinnamon and 1 cup sugar.
Heat in a saucepan.
Pour over biscuit mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven approximately 45 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar with 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a bowl.
Open 1 can of biscuits at a time.
Cut each biscuit into 8 pieces.
Coat pieces of biscuit with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Put into Bundt pan that has been greased and layer with 1/2 cup pecan pieces.
Mix in a boiler the last ingredients.
Bring to a boil and pour over biscuits.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let set in pan for 10 minutes.
Better to serve hot.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: In saucepan, combine beef, soup and broth.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add corn and uncooked macaroni.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Toss together crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes more.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken madrid
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet over medium heat. Add chicken. Brown on both sides and remove from pan.
Put onion, peppers and garlic in pan. Saute, stirring constantly, until onions are translucent.
Return chicken to pan.
Pour in tomatoes.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes. Cover with fresh parsley. Serve over rice.

title: aunt millie's pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in tube pan.
Put in cold oven.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Mix
bread crumbs, cracker crumbs, egg, lemon juice and soup together.
Add
salmon,
salt
and	pepper, mixing well. Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mamaw's cooked chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in skillet.
When it begins to boil, cook one minute, stirring over fire constantly.
Let cool and spread.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a large skillet brown sausage; drain well and set aside. In a large bowl, mix milk, eggs, dry mustard, salt and pepper. Mix well; then add onion, green chilies, sausage and bread.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Can be mixed up the night before and stored in the refrigerator.
The next morning let sit at room temperature for 15 minutes before baking.

title: hamburg barley soup
directions: Brown beef.
Add all ingredients, except potatoes, carrots and beans.
Simmer for 45 minutes. Add carrots and cook for 10 minutes. Add potatoes and cook for 10 minutes. Add the beans in the last 10 minutes of cooking time.

title: iceberg ring
directions: Dissolve the gelatin and salt in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in the cold water and vinegar.
Chill until mixture is slightly thickened.
Fold in the lettuce and green onion.
Pour into 5-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
If desired, fill the center with tuna salad.

title: 1940 carrot relish
directions: Chop carrots with medium blade in food chopper.
Cook until done.
Run other ingredients through chopper.
Cook with spices for 15 minutes.
Can in pint jars.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken with seasoning, reserve broth; cut in bite size. Saute celery, onion and green pepper in butter.
Cook spaghetti in broth; drain excess broth; mix chicken, spaghetti and vegetables; add soup, cheese and pimento.
Place in buttered dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: zucchini chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Break spaghetti in half. Cook according to package directions; drain. In medium saucepan, cook bacon until crisp. Blend in soup. Add zucchini and milk. Cook until zucchini is tender. Stir in Mozzarella, then add spaghetti and chicken. Pour mixture into 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 40 minutes.

title: sausage and noodle bake
directions: Brown sausage with chopped onion.
Prepare fine noodles (cook and drain) with 1 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Heat and blend chicken soup, milk and shredded cheese.
Combine all the ingredients.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: "blanc mange"
directions: Scald milk on top of double boiler.
Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch together and slowly stir into hot milk.
Continue to cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens.
Cover and continue to cook for 15 or 20 minutes or until no raw, starchy taste remains.
Beat egg and pour blanc mange into it.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Chill.
Serve with hot chocolate sauce.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt together the chocolate and butter.
Mix at high speed eggs, sugar and flour, then add vanilla and pecans.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Bake in greased pie pan at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: 24 hour layered salad
directions: Layer in order given.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: dijon potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; chill.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: beef roast
directions: Just sprinkle nutmeg on the roast along with the salt and pepper.
Start out with a small amount to see if family likes it with the nutmeg.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and serve.

title: coffee punchroswell, new mexico
directions: Combine coffee, water and sugar and cook 8 min. over medium (do not boil).

title: rocky road dessert pie
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease and dust 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie pan.
Reserve 1 2/3 cup cake mix.
Beat remaining mix with water, oil
and
eggs
in	medium	bowl at low speed, scraping constantly 30	seconds.
Beat	on medium 2 minutes.
Spread in pie pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: oatmeal pie(poor man's pecan pie)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Should be dark golden brown.

title: chicken strips in garlic butter
directions: Dredge strips in flour, salt and pepper.
Fry in Crisco or butter until browned.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Melt 1 stick of margarine.
Add garlic and pour over strips.
Pour in broth.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic powder and parsley. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over noodles.

title: apple honeys
directions: Core apples and place in 9-inch glass baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients except 1/4 cup honey.
Pour this mixture over apples.
Pour remaining honey over all.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes or until tender.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain green peas.
Add	mayonnaise and remaining ingredients. Chill for 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Roll steak in extra flour and brown in butter or margarine. Stir in soup mix.
Add consomme.
Blend 2 tablespoons flour (or more if needed) with sour cream and add to meat mixture, stirring until thickened.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 4 to 6.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water and peaches. Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Cool and add lemon juice.

title: tuna-pea casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a 2 quart baking dish. Then bake at 350 for 30-35 minutes.
Crumble crackers over top. Bake 5 minutes.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine spinach, cream cheese, Parmesan and soup mix.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Lightly coat a baking sheet with cooking spray.
Unroll dough.
Press perforations to seal.
Spoon and spread filling evenly over dough to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Place on prepared baking sheet.
Bake until golden, about 15 minutes.
Remove; place on wire rack and cool slightly.
Serve warm.

title: cauliflower with browned crumbs
directions: Heat cauliflower thoroughly.
Brown crumbs in butter; add paprika and sprinkle mixture over hot cauliflower.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler, stirring frequently.
Add everything else and simmer for 30 min.
May freeze and refreeze.

title: fudgiest brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in top of double boiler; cool slightly.
Beat in remaining ingredients by hand.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until set or about 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.
Preparation Time: 0:45.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Beat egg and sugar together.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to egg and sugar.
Add salt and 4 cups of flour.
Stir with spoon.
Add melted butter and stir.
Add 3 cups of flour.
Knead well.
Let rise until size has doubled.
Shape into rolls and let rolls rise about an hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Dough can be kept in refrigerator.

title: e z raisin cake
directions: Boil the raisins in the 2 cups water for 10 minutes.
Add the butter or margarine; let this mixture cool.
Blend the flour, soda, salt, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg together in a saucepan. Fold in the cooled raisin mixture with the blended spices and flour.
Grease a 10 x 10 x 2-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 36 minutes.

title: chicken yum yum
directions: Take 1 pkg. pastry shells & cut on perforated lines. Lay flat on cookie sheet. Boil chicken until done. Cut into bite size pieces. Lay chicken on shells. Sprinkle with cheese & soup mix that is mixed with enough milk to make thick creamy mix. Cover with another shell. Cook until golden brown at 350°. Remove and cover with cheese and sour cream. Replace in oven until cheese is melted. Makes 2 servings.

title: tomato, eggplant and cheese casserole
directions: Peel and finely chop onion and garlic.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a saucepan and fry onion and garlic until soft.
Peel, seed and chop tomatoes.
Add to pan with 1/2 teaspoon basil and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook for 30 to 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar and flour.
Stir in the corn, butter and milk.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or longer.
(Test for doneness with a toothpick.)

title: cream cheese chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well. Combine salt, baking powder, baking soda and flour.
Stir in flour mixture until smooth.
Add TV chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoons about 1 1/2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: hawaiian fudge
directions: Cook this mixture to soft ball 238°. Remove from heat and add 2 tbsp. of butter and 1 c. nuts. Beat until creamy and pour into shallow dish. Cut into blocks when cool.

title: pecan creams
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until set but not brown. While warm, roll in powdered sugar; cool.
Roll in powdered sugar again.

title: oatmeal brownies(low-fat)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and blend well.
Add egg whites and blend well.
Combine remaining ingredients in another bowl, then mix all together.
Pour batter into an 8-inch square pan, coated with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 23 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into 12 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together, then mix in order the oil, milk, eggs and corn.
Mix all together.
Cook in Pyrex 9 x 9-inch dish in a 450° oven until lightly browned on top.

title: vegetable pot pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients except biscuits; pour into baking pan.
Top with can of biscuits; press biscuits flat, then put on top of pie covering entire pie.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan. Can also bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for approximately 35 minutes.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Remove	all
sinew
from venison.
Cut into bite sizes. Apply salt,
pepper
and flour, then fry.
After frying, take grease venison is fried in.
Add McCormick beef stroganoff mix (after mixing
with
water),
then
add the venison to gravy. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over white rice.
Add the sour cream as preferred.
(Two pounds of round steak with sinew removed may be substituted for tenders.)

title: preserved children
directions: Mix children and dogs well together.
Sprinkle the field with flowers.
Spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in the sun. When brown, set away to cool in the bath tub.

title: double thick malted shake
directions: Put the 1/2 cup milk into a large cup and then add 1 scoop chocolate ice cream.
Mix until the ice cream is melted.
If you want to, ask Mom if you can use the blender or put it in a large bowl and use an eggbeater.
After it is mixed, add the rest of the ice cream and add the malt.
Mix until foamy.

title: salmon fillet with mustard glaze
directions: Rinse salmon fillet and pat dry.
Place fillet, skin side down, on a piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil placed in 10 to 15-inch pan.
With scissors, cut foil around fish; discard the rim.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles in large amount boiling salted water until tender; drain, rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients except Mozzarella. Place half the noodles in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with half the cottage cheese filling.
Add of Mozzarella and half meat sauce. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Take cranberries and grind them up.
Add sugar and can crushed pineapple.
Take celery and cut up in small pieces.
Add celery and nuts to cranberries.
Prepare jello as directed and then pour over cranberries; mix good.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: festive-red and green salad
directions: Marinate for 2 hours or overnight in long low bowl.
Marinade is simply 1 (8 ounce) bottle of red wine vinegar or South Seas salad dressing.

title: microwave meal for two
directions: Take 1 head of cabbage or as much as you want to eat, chop into a Corning or microwave dish.
Cover and place in microwave. Cook on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir cabbage and cook on High for additional 1 to 2 minutes or until it suits you.
Season to taste and add a couple of pats of butter or margarine.
Let sit while you finish cooking rest of your dinner.

title: granola - new age
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Ready to eat by itself.

title: beef and cabbage taco casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl, toss together the potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 1/8 teaspoon onion salt.
Press into the bottom and up sides of a greased 1-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a 3 quart oblong baking dish combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper.
Stir in cooked veggies and chicken.

title: spagetti
directions: Take a bowl.
Then when they are soft put the grave and meat bloul in Then let it sit far awile and then eat it.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine broccoli, onion and chicken broth.
Simmer 10 minutes. Pour in blender; mix until smooth.
Melt butter in pan and add flour, half and half, salt and pepper.
Stir in broccoli mixture. Cook about 45 minutes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: orange punch
directions: Chill the cans of juice, if possible.
Mix all ingredients in punch bowl and stir.
Ice may be used in glass.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Make into medium balls and roll in sugar mixture (4 tablespoons sugar and 3 teaspoons of cinnamon).
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Skin, debone and cook chicken breasts.
Shred into bite-sized pieces and set-aside.
Tear lettuce into bite sized pieces.
Toss all ingredients together except noodles.

title: eggnog
directions: Combine well beaten eggs, condensed milk, vanilla and salt. Gently beat in milk.
Fold in whipped cream.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Float ice cream block to keep cold.

title: butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cream together the butter and sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Pour the batter into the greased Bundt pan and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or knife inserted in center of cake comes out clean.

title: gorgonzola salad
directions: Process the oil and garlic in food processor or blender. Store in a covered jar in refrigerator.
Grate the cheese over salad.
Pour vinegar and oil mixture over salad as desired.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, combine all except parsley; mix thoroughly. Put in refrigerator 15 minutes.
Shape into ball; roll in parsley. Coat well.
Refrigerate 20 minutes more.

title: banana bread
directions: Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves, different and very good.

title: chicken breast
directions: Put ingredients in a covered casserole; bake until done.

title: rissoles(english potatoes)
directions: Boil potatoes and drain.
Add milk and grated corned beef; mash.
Fry in patties.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover and boil 3 minutes.
Remove cover and boil at 250° or until a hard ball stage, then add butter and peanuts.
Cook slowly to 300° or a hard crack stage.
Add vanilla and soda to mixture quickly.
Pour into greased pan or platter.
Let stand one minute (or until like a pancake which will turn out clean).
Yields 2 pounds.

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Spray a Bundt pan with nonstick vegetable spray. Place rolls in pan. Mix dry pudding, brown sugar and pecans. Pour over rolls until covered. Pour melted butter over top. Leave out overnight to rise. In the morning, bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix bran and boiling water.
Add sugar, eggs and oil.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Pour into papered muffin tins and bake at 400 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter will keep six weeks in refrigerator (tightly covered).
Makes 6-8 dozen.

title: brandied peaches
directions: Blanch peaches in boiling water.
Peel, slice and cool.
Bring sugar and water to a boil; add brandy.
Pour over peaches and let sit for 24 hours or longer.
Delicious.

title: russian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a screw-top jar.
Shake well. Refrigerate.

title: monster cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine brown sugar, granulated sugar and Crisco in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Beat in eggs; beat in peanut butter, corn syrup, baking soda and vanilla.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips with spoon.
Fill ice cream scoop that holds 1/4 cup with dough (or use 1/4 cup measure).
Level with knife (or form dough into 2-inch balls).

Drop 3 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 11 minutes or until just beginning to brown. Cool on baking sheet 5 minutes before removing to cooling rack. Yields 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: apple crunch
directions: In a large bowl, mix apples, brown sugar, cinnamon and salt until apples are coated. Place mixture in a 10 x 10 pan and put Crunch evenly on top.

title: dark delicious apple cake
directions: Place apples in bowl and toss with sugar.
In a large mixing bowl beat eggs, oil and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt in bowl.
Add flour mixture alternately with apples to egg mixture.
Beat until mixed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: holly taters
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and then put together in large Ziploc bag with potatoes.
Shake until potatoes are coated.
Melt 1/2 cup butter.
Drizzle over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Turn after 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add mashed bananas; beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour and nuts, mixing well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up cauliflower and onions.
Fry bacon crisp; add to cauliflower and onions.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and milk.
Pour over cauliflower and mix.
Set in refrigerator.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Break bread into cubes.
Set aside - Beat eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla together.
Stir in bread cubes.
Add raisins and stir. Pour into well-greased baking dish. Bake at 325 degrees until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water; should be about 3 cups when done.
Mash coarsely and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ham au gratin
directions: Cook asparagus and drain well.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put onion in and saute onions with the mushrooms.
Remove from heat.
Put ham in skillet.
Grate cheese and add to skillet. Mix rest of ingredients.
Add and mix it all very well.
Add asparagus and mix lightly.
Line sides of casserole with toast. Cover with mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and some remaining bread crumbs.
Broil 5-inches from heat for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and browned.

title: all bran rolls
directions: Mix 1 cup boiling water, cereal, margarine, salt, sugar and eggs; cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add yeast mixture to cereal mixture.
Stir well.
Add eggs and enough flour to make soft dough.
Refrigerate overnight.
Make rolls into desired shape; let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: pecan snowballs
directions: Cream butter, vanilla and sugar together until fluffy; add salt and flour, sifted together.
Add pecans; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields 50 cookies.

title: original salvation army world war i doughnuts
directions: Put flour in shallow pan; add salt, baking powder, sugar and spices.
Rub in butter with fingertips.
Add the well beaten egg and milk and stir thoroughly.
Toss on floured board.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Shape, fry and drain.

title: randy's pork chops
directions: Cut all fat from chops and brown on both sides.
In a small bowl, mix soup, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup.
In an ovenware dish, place 2 or 3 browned chops, a large dollop of sauce and top with onion slice.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except eggs.
Beat eggs well and add to mixture.
Blend and bake in shallow baking dish (drizzle with honey before baking).
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cinnamon thumbs
directions: Mix butter, flour, vanilla and 5 tablespoons sugar.
Roll small amount of dough into a thumb-like shape.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
In a separate bowl, mix 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 cup sugar.
Let cinnamon thumbs cool slightly, then roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Grease a shallow pan and set aside.
Fill sink half full of cold water.
Ina saucepan, combine sugar, milk, cocoa and syrup. Cook while stirring over medium-high heat.
Boil until soft ball stage or 234°.
Remove saucepan from heat, add butter and vanilla and place in sink of water.
Cool slightly, then beat well until mixture thickens and loses its glossy shine.
Pour quickly into greased pan.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Cut when cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese until soft.
Add peanut butter, sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Put in plain or chocolate graham cracker crust.
Swirl with thin lines of chocolate syrup on top. Chill about 1 hour.
Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients and put in casserole. Top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350°
oven for 30 minutes. Serves 7 to 8.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Mix all ingredients with ground beef. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place drained bacon and sausage along with croutons in the pan.
Mix eggs, milk and mushroom soup; pour over croutons and meat.
Top casserole with shredded cheese and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until eggs are firm and cheese is bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips, in greased casserole. Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken with dill
directions: Saute chicken breasts in oil until browned.
Add dill, salt, pepper and vegetables.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: vegetable juice
directions: Stew all the ingredients until tender.
Simmer until tomatoes are softened.
Put through a food mill.
To juice, add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon sugar per quart.
Put in quart jars.
Process 20 minutes.
The next thing to V-8 juice and costs a lot less. Serve well chilled.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water, pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add drained pineapple.
Cover with marshmallows.
Chill until set.
In a saucepan combine beaten egg, sugar, cornstarch and 1 cup pineapple juice (can add water to make 1 cup, if not enough juice).
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Cool.
Spread over Jell-O mixture.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Spread over top of mixture and chill.
Sprinkle 1 cup Cheddar cheese on top of Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture, if desired.
Chill and serve, cut into squares.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Combine chicken, celery, grapes, almonds, parsley, salt and mayonnaise; mix well.
Serve on lettuce, avocado half or in scooped out tomato or pineapple half.
Garnish with olives and chicken slices.

title: creamed ham and asparagus
directions: In a saucepan, cook asparagus in small amount of water until tender, drain and set aside.
In a medium pan mix cornstarch and 2 tablespoons milk.
Add butter, salt and pepper and remaining milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Add parsley, ham, eggs, cheese and asparagus.
Cook and stir over low heat until ham is warmed and cheese is melted.
Serve on toast or biscuits.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple garlic pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients except chops; mix well.
Place the chops in a shallow baking dish and pour marinade over them. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove the chops from the marinade; boil 5 inches from the heat 4 to 5 minutes per side. (These can be pan-fried also.)

title: velvet fudge
directions: Melt butter; add cocoa, Karo and salt.
Mix sugar and milk; add to butter and cocoa.
Mix well and cook to soft ball stage when tried in cold water.
Let cool.
Add nuts, if desired.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Work with hands if necessary.
Shape into roll and slice.

title: oreo cookie ice cream
directions: Left ice cream soften.
Crush Oreo cookies.
Combine all ingredients and freeze.

title: easy $175 cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and melted margarine and press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Top with pecans and chocolate chips. Mix confectioners sugar, remaining 2 eggs and cream cheese. Pour over cake mix base. Bake at 350° until bubbly and golden, about 45 minutes. When cool, cut into squares.

title: caramel crackers
directions: Baking Temperature: 250°.
Baking Time: 1 hour.

title: annette's mexican glorias
